36/*
37 * The data structures used:
38 * . temporary pointer descriptor (TPD) structure, used while processing a
39 * single statement. This is used to build the subsequent data structures.
40 * descriptor type, symbol table pointer, integer value
41 * . pointer source descriptor (PSD), used to describe the pointers assigned
42 * in the program. This is quite like a persistent PD; the number of these
43 * is the 'width' of the data flow value carried between blocks.
44 * . pointer assignment (PA), describes the LHS with a PSD, and the RHS
45 * with either another PSD, for assignment like p=q, or ++p, or with
46 * a pointer target entry if the RHS is a constant address, like p=&a
47 * or p=NULL.
48 *
49 * tpdx = index to temporary pointer descriptor
50 * psdx = index to pointer source descriptor
51 * ptex = index to pointer target entry
52 * atex = index to actual target entry
53 * asx = index to assignment table
54 * sl = slot number
55 * sptr = symbol table pointer
56 * bihx = block table index
57 * ilix = ili table index
58 * iltx = ilt table index
59 * nmex = nme table index
60 */
61
62/*
63 * This is a temporary pointer descriptor (TPD) data structure, to hold
64 * addresses
65 * while processing a single statement
66 */
67typedef struct {
68 int type;
69 int sym;
70 int val;
71 int link;
72} TPD;
73
74static STG_DECLARE(gtpd, TPD) = { STG_INIT };

76#if DEBUG
77#define TTYPE(tpdx) \
78 gtpd.stg_base[tpdx >= 0 && tpdx < gtpd.stg_avail \
79 ? tpdx \
80 : (interr("bad TTYPE index", tpdx, 4), 0)] \
81 .type
82#define TSYM(tpdx) \
83 gtpd.stg_base[tpdx >= 0 && tpdx < gtpd.stg_avail \
84 ? tpdx \
85 : (interr("bad TSYM index", tpdx, 4), 0)] \
86 .sym
87#define TVAL(tpdx) \
88 gtpd.stg_base[tpdx >= 0 && tpdx < gtpd.stg_avail \
89 ? tpdx \
90 : (interr("bad TVAL index", tpdx, 4), 0)] \
91 .val
92#define TLINK(tpdx) \
93 gtpd.stg_base[tpdx >= 0 && tpdx < gtpd.stg_avail \
94 ? tpdx \
95 : (interr("bad TLINK index", tpdx, 4), 0)] \
96 .link
97#else
98#define TTYPE(tpdx) gtpd.stg_base[tpdx].type
99#define TSYM(tpdx) gtpd.stg_base[tpdx].sym
100#define TVAL(tpdx) gtpd.stg_base[tpdx].val
101#define TLINK(tpdx) gtpd.stg_base[tpdx].link

104/* unknown target */
105#define TT_UNINIT 0x100
106/* unknown target */
107#define TT_UNK 0x110
108/* unknown global ... used for type target or for dummy pointer source */
109#define TT_GLOB 0x120
110/* precise symbol */
111#define TT_PSYM 0x130
112/* imprecise symbol */
113#define TT_ISYM 0x140
114/* anonymous memory, from IPA */
115#define TT_ANON 0x150
116/* dynamically allocated memory, also from IPA */
117#define TT_GDYN 0x160
118/* imprecise dynamically allocated memory, also from IPA */
119#define TT_IGDYN 0x170
120/* dynamically allocated memory, from this function call */
121#define TT_LDYN 0x180
122/* imprecise dynamically allocated memory, from this function call */
123#define TT_ILDYN 0x190
124/* constant address, used for NULL */
125#define TT_CON 0x1a0
126/* indirection */
127#define TT_IND 0x1b0
128/* imprecise indirection */
129#define TT_IIND 0x1c0
130/* member */
131#define TT_MEM 0x1d0
132/* nonlocal memory */
133#define TT_NLOC 0x1e0
134
135#define TTE_NULL -1
136
137/* MUSTFLAG is set if this is a must point to situation
138 IMPFLAG is set if this is an imprecise descriptor */
139#define TTMUSTFLAG 1
140#define TTIMPFLAG 2
141/* remove MUST flag */
142#define TTMASKMUST(typ) ((typ)&0xfffe)
143/* remove MUST and IMP flags */
144#define TTMASK(typ) ((typ)&0xfffd)
145#define TTMUST(typ) ((typ)&TTMUSTFLAG)
146#define TTIMP(typ) ((typ)&TTIMPFLAG)

148/*
149 * this is a temporary pointer source descriptor (PSD)
150 * it looks a lot like NMEs (but no subscripts, yes struct members)
151 */
152typedef struct {
153 int type;
154 int parent;
155 int sym;
156 int next; /* next PSD with same parent */
157 int child; /* child PSD */
158 int slot;
159 int hashlk;
160} PSD;
161
162static struct {
163 STG_MEMBERS(PSD);
164 int *slot;
165 int nslots;
166} gpsd = {STG_INIT, NULL, 0};
167
168#if DEBUG
169#define PSD_TYPE(psdx) \
170 gpsd.stg_base[psdx >= 0 && psdx < gpsd.stg_avail \
171 ? psdx \
172 : (interr("bad PSD_TYPE index", psdx, 4), 0)] \
173 .type
174#define PSD_PARENT(psdx) \
175 gpsd.stg_base[psdx >= 0 && psdx < gpsd.stg_avail \
176 ? psdx \
177 : (interr("bad PSD_PARENT index", psdx, 4), 0)] \
178 .parent
179#define PSD_SYM(psdx) \
180 gpsd.stg_base[psdx >= 0 && psdx < gpsd.stg_avail \
181 ? psdx \
182 : (interr("bad PSD_SYM index", psdx, 4), 0)] \
183 .sym
184#define PSD_CHILD(psdx) \
185 gpsd.stg_base[psdx >= 0 && psdx < gpsd.stg_avail \
186 ? psdx \
187 : (interr("bad PSD_CHILD index", psdx, 4), 0)] \
188 .child
189#define PSD_NEXT(psdx) \
190 gpsd.stg_base[psdx >= 0 && psdx < gpsd.stg_avail \
191 ? psdx \
192 : (interr("bad PSD_NEXT index", psdx, 4), 0)] \
193 .next
194#define PSD_HASHLK(psdx) \
195 gpsd.stg_base[psdx >= 0 && psdx < gpsd.stg_avail \
196 ? psdx \
197 : (interr("bad PSD_HASHLK index", psdx, 4), 0)] \
198 .hashlk
199#define PSD_SLOT(psdx) \
200 gpsd.stg_base[psdx >= 0 && psdx < gpsd.stg_avail \
201 ? psdx \
202 : (interr("bad PSD_SLOT index", psdx, 4), 0)] \
203 .slot
204#define SLOT(sl) \
205 gpsd.slot[sl >= 0 && sl <= gpsd.nslots \
206 ? sl \
207 : (interr("bad SLOT index", sl, 4), 0)]
208#else
209#define PSD_TYPE(psdx) gpsd.stg_base[psdx].type
210#define PSD_PARENT(psdx) gpsd.stg_base[psdx].parent
211#define PSD_SYM(psdx) gpsd.stg_base[psdx].sym
212#define PSD_CHILD(psdx) gpsd.stg_base[psdx].child
213#define PSD_NEXT(psdx) gpsd.stg_base[psdx].next
214#define PSD_HASHLK(psdx) gpsd.stg_base[psdx].hashlk
215#define PSD_SLOT(psdx) gpsd.stg_base[psdx].slot
216#define SLOT(sl) gpsd.slot[sl]
217#endif

466#if DEBUG
467static void
468puttds(int tdsx)
469{
470 switch (TTYPE(tdsx)) {
471 case TT_UNK:
472 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "Unknown");
473 break;
474 case TT_UNINIT:
475 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "Uninit");
476 break;
477 case TT_PSYM:
478 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "%d:%s", TSYM(tdsx), SYMNAME(TSYM(tdsx)));
479 break;
480 case TT_ISYM:
481 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "%d:%s?", TSYM(tdsx), SYMNAME(TSYM(tdsx)));
482 break;
483 case TT_ANON:
484 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, ".anon%d.", TVAL(tdsx));
485 break;
486 case TT_GDYN:
487 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, ".dyn%d.", TVAL(tdsx));
488 break;
489 case TT_IGDYN:
490 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, ".dyn%d?.", TVAL(tdsx));
491 break;
492 case TT_LDYN:
493 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, ".ldyn%d.", TVAL(tdsx));
494 break;
495 case TT_ILDYN:
496 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, ".ldyn%d?.", TVAL(tdsx));
497 break;
498 case TT_CON:
499 if (TVAL(tdsx) == 0) {
500 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, ".null.");
501 } else {
502 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, ".con.");
503 }
504 break;
505 case TT_IND:
506 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "*");
507 puttds(TVAL(tdsx));
508 break;
509 case TT_IIND:
510 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "*(");
511 puttds(TVAL(tdsx));
512 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, ")?");
513 break;
514 case TT_MEM:
515 puttds(TVAL(tdsx));
516 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, ".%s", SYMNAME(TSYM(tdsx)));
517 break;
518 case TT_GLOB:
519 /* dummy, used when all globals might be modified */
520 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, ".glob.");
521 break;
522 case TT_NLOC:
523 /* pseudo target for any nonlocal variable */
524 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, ".nloc.");
525 break;
526 default:
527 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "?? %d:%d:%d", TTYPE(tdsx), TSYM(tdsx), TVAL(tdsx));
528 break;
529 }
530} /* puttds */

532static void
533putpsd(int psdx)
534{
535 switch (PSD_TYPE(psdx)) {
536 case TT_PSYM:
537 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "%d:%s", PSD_SYM(psdx), SYMNAME(PSD_SYM(psdx)));
538 break;
539 case TT_ISYM:
540 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "%d:%s?", PSD_SYM(psdx), SYMNAME(PSD_SYM(psdx)));
541 break;
542 case TT_IND:
543 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "*(");
544 putpsd(PSD_PARENT(psdx));
545 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, ")");
546 break;
547 case TT_IIND:
548 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "*(");
549 putpsd(PSD_PARENT(psdx));
550 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, ")?");
551 break;
552 case TT_MEM:
553 putpsd(PSD_PARENT(psdx));
554 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, ".%s", SYMNAME(PSD_SYM(psdx)));
555 break;
556 case TT_GLOB:
557 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, ".glob.");
558 break;
559 case TT_NLOC:
560 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, ".nloc!.");
561 break;
562 case TT_UNK:
563 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "Unknown!");
564 break;
565 case TT_UNINIT:
566 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "Uninit!");
567 break;
568 default:
569 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, ".??%d:%d.", PSD_TYPE(psdx), PSD_SYM(psdx));
570 break;
571 }
572} /* putpsd */

574static void
575putpte(int ptex)
576{
577 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "[%d:%d]", ptex, TPTE_APTEX(ptex));
578 switch (TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(ptex))) {
579 case TT_UNINIT:
580 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "&.uninit.");
581 break;
582 case TT_UNK:
583 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "&.unk.");
584 break;
585 case TT_PSYM:
586 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "&%d:%s", TPTE_SPTR(ptex), SYMNAME(TPTE_SPTR(ptex)));
587 break;
588 case TT_ISYM:
589 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "&%d:%s?", TPTE_SPTR(ptex), SYMNAME(TPTE_SPTR(ptex)));
590 break;
591 case TT_ANON:
592 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "&anon:%d", TPTE_VAL(ptex));
593 break;
594 case TT_GDYN:
595 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "&dyn:%d", TPTE_VAL(ptex));
596 break;
597 case TT_IGDYN:
598 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "&dyn:%d?", TPTE_VAL(ptex));
599 break;
600 case TT_LDYN:
601 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "&ldyn:%d", TPTE_VAL(ptex));
602 break;
603 case TT_ILDYN:
604 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "&ldyn:%d?", TPTE_VAL(ptex));
605 break;
606 case TT_CON:
607 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "&con:%d", TPTE_VAL(ptex));
608 break;
609 case TT_NLOC:
610 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "&.nloc.");
611 break;
612 case TT_IND:
613 /* should not appear */
614 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "*(");
615 putpte(TPTE_VAL(ptex));
616 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, ")");
617 break;
618 case TT_IIND:
619 /* should not appear */
620 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "*(");
621 putpte(TPTE_VAL(ptex));
622 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, ")?");
623 break;
624 case TT_MEM:
625 /* should not appear */
626 putpte(TPTE_VAL(ptex));
627 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, ".%s", SYMNAME(TPTE_SPTR(ptex)));
628 break;
629 case TT_GLOB:
630 /* should not appear */
631 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, ".glob%d!.", TPTE_VAL(ptex));
632 break;
633 default:
634 /* should not appear */
635 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "???%d:%d", TPTE_TYPE(ptex), TPTE_VAL(ptex));
636 break;
637 }
638 if (TPTE_STRIDE(ptex) > 0) {
639 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "(::%d)", TPTE_STRIDE(ptex));
640 }
641 if (TTMUST(TPTE_TYPE(ptex))) {
642 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "!");
643 }
644} /* putpte */

646static void
647putassign(int asx)
648{
649 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, " as:%d node:%d ", asx, ASNODE(asx));
650 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "std:%d ", ASILT(asx));
651 putpsd(ASLHS(asx));
652 switch (ASTYPE(asx)) {
653 case AS_DIRECT:
654 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, " <= ");
655 putpte(ASRHS(asx));
656 break;
657 case AS_ADD_DIRECT:
658 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, " <+= ");
659 putpte(ASRHS(asx));
660 break;
661 case AS_INDIRECT:
662 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, " <== ");
663 putpsd(ASRHS(asx));
664 break;
665 case AS_ADD_INDIRECT:
666 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, " <+== ");
667 putpsd(ASRHS(asx));
668 break;
669 case AS_INIT:
670 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, " <= ");
671 putpte(ASRHS(asx));
672 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, " (init)");
673 break;
674 case AS_CLEAR:
675 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, " <== CLEAR");
676 break;
677 case AS_UNK:
678 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, " <== UNKNOWN");
679 break;
680 default:
681 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, " <<-- type:%d(%d)", ASTYPE(asx), ASRHS(asx));
682 break;
683 }
684 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, " stride(%d)", ASSTRIDE(asx));
685 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "\n");
686} /* putassign */

767/*
768 * return TRUE if this source is a global symbol,
769 * or is an indirection that might point to a global symbol.
770 */
771static int
772is_source_global(int psdx)
773{
774 int sptr, parentpsdx, sl, ptex;
775 switch (PSD_TYPE(psdx)) {
776 case TT_PSYM:
777 case TT_ISYM:
778 /* is this a global symbol? */
779 sptr = PSD_SYM(psdx);
780 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_EXTERN || SCG(sptr) == SC_CMBLK) {
781 return TRUE;
782 }
783 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_BASED && MIDNUMG(sptr)) {
784 sptr = MIDNUMG(sptr);
785 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_EXTERN || SCG(sptr) == SC_CMBLK) {
786 return TRUE;
787 }
788 }
789 break;
790 case TT_IND:
791 case TT_IIND:
792 /* look at parent */
793 /* look at pointer targets of the parent */
794 parentpsdx = PSD_PARENT(psdx);
795 if (is_source_global(parentpsdx))
796 return TRUE;
797 sl = PSD_SLOT(parentpsdx);
798 if (LHEAD(sl) == TPTE_UNK)
799 return TRUE;
800 for (ptex = LHEAD(sl); ptex > 0; ptex = TPTE_NEXT(ptex)) {
801 switch (TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(ptex))) {
802 case TT_UNK:
803 case TT_UNINIT:
804 return TRUE;
805 case TT_PSYM:
806 case TT_ISYM:
807 sptr = TPTE_SPTR(ptex);
808 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_EXTERN || SCG(sptr) == SC_CMBLK) {
809 return TRUE;
810 }
811 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_BASED && MIDNUMG(sptr)) {
812 sptr = MIDNUMG(sptr);
813 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_EXTERN || SCG(sptr) == SC_CMBLK) {
814 return TRUE;
815 }
816 }
817 break;
818 case TT_NLOC:
819 return TRUE; /* all we know is something nonlocal, may be global */
820 case TT_ANON:
821 case TT_GDYN:
822 case TT_IGDYN:
823 case TT_LDYN:
824 case TT_ILDYN:
825 case TT_CON:
826 break;
827 default:
828 /* real error */
829 interr("bad PTE type", TPTE_TYPE(ptex), ERR_Fatal);
830 return TRUE;
831 }
832 }
833 return FALSE;
834 break;
835 case TT_GLOB:
836 return TRUE;
837 case TT_UNK:
838 case TT_UNINIT:
839 return TRUE;
840 }
841 return FALSE;
842} /* is_source_global */
843
844/*
845 * return TRUE if this source is a global symbol that we know to be safe
846 */
847static int
848safe_symbol(int psdx)
849{
850 int sptr;
851 switch (PSD_TYPE(psdx)) {
852 case TT_PSYM:
853 case TT_ISYM:
854 /* is this a global symbol? */
855 sptr = PSD_SYM(psdx);
856 if (VOLG(sptr))
857 return FALSE;
858 break;
859 /* we don't know anything about other pointer sources */
860 }
861 return FALSE;
862} /* safe_symbol */
863
864/*
865 * return TRUE if this source is a global or static symbol,
866 * or is an indirection that might point to a global or static symbol.
867 */
868static int
869is_source_nonlocal(int psdx)
870{
871 int sptr, parentpsdx, sl, ptex;
872 switch (PSD_TYPE(psdx)) {
873 case TT_PSYM:
874 case TT_ISYM:
875 /* is this a global symbol? */
876 sptr = PSD_SYM(psdx);
877 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_EXTERN || SCG(sptr) == SC_CMBLK ||
878 SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY || (gbl.internal > 1 && !INTERNALG(sptr))) {
879 return TRUE;
880 }
881 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_BASED && MIDNUMG(sptr)) {
882 sptr = MIDNUMG(sptr);
883 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_EXTERN || SCG(sptr) == SC_CMBLK ||
884 SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY || (gbl.internal > 1 && !INTERNALG(sptr))) {
885 return TRUE;
886 }
887 }
888 break;
889 case TT_IND:
890 case TT_IIND:
891 /* look at pointer targets of the parent */
892 parentpsdx = PSD_PARENT(psdx);
893 if (is_source_nonlocal(parentpsdx))
894 return TRUE;
895 sl = PSD_SLOT(parentpsdx);
896 if (LHEAD(sl) == TPTE_UNK)
897 return TRUE;
898 for (ptex = LHEAD(sl); ptex > 0; ptex = TPTE_NEXT(ptex)) {
899 switch (TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(ptex))) {
900 case TT_UNK:
901 case TT_UNINIT:
902 return TRUE;
903 case TT_PSYM:
904 case TT_ISYM:
905 sptr = TPTE_SPTR(ptex);
906 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_EXTERN || SCG(sptr) == SC_CMBLK ||
907 SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY || (gbl.internal > 1 && !INTERNALG(sptr))) {
908 return TRUE;
909 }
910 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_BASED && MIDNUMG(sptr)) {
911 sptr = MIDNUMG(sptr);
912 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_EXTERN || SCG(sptr) == SC_CMBLK ||
913 SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY || (gbl.internal > 1 && !INTERNALG(sptr))) {
914 return TRUE;
915 }
916 }
917 break;
918 case TT_NLOC: /* all we know is something nonlocal, may be global */
919 case TT_ANON: /* anonymous nonlocal */
920 case TT_GLOB:
921 return TRUE;
922 case TT_GDYN:
923 case TT_IGDYN:
924 case TT_LDYN:
925 case TT_ILDYN:
926 case TT_CON:
927 break;
928 default:
929 /* real error */
930 interr("bad PTE type", TPTE_TYPE(ptex), ERR_Warning);
931 return TRUE;
932 }
933 }
934 return FALSE;
935 break;
936 case TT_GLOB:
937 return TRUE;
938 case TT_UNINIT:
939 case TT_UNK:
940 return TRUE;
941 }
942 return FALSE;
943} /* is_source_nonlocal */
944
945/*
946 * add a new pointer source descriptor to the table
947 * if this is an LHS reference, make sure it has a slot number
948 */
949static void
950add_psd(int tpdx, int type, int parent, int sym, bool lhs)
951{
952 int val, psdx, t;
953
954 t = TTMASK(type);
955 val = (int)((t ^ sym ^ parent) & 0x7fff) % PSDHSZ;
956 for (psdx = psdhsh[val]; psdx > 0; psdx = PSD_HASHLK(psdx)) {
957 if (PSD_TYPE(psdx) == t && PSD_PARENT(psdx) == parent &&
958 PSD_SYM(psdx) == sym) {
959 if (tpdx)
960 TLINK(tpdx) = psdx;
961 if (TTIMP(type)) {
962 PSD_TYPE(psdx) |= TTIMPFLAG;
963 }
964 if (lhs && PSD_SLOT(psdx) == 0) {
965 PSD_SLOT(psdx) = gpsd.nslots++;
966 }
967 return;
968 }
969 }
970 psdx = STG_NEXT(gpsd);
971 PSD_TYPE(psdx) = type;
972 PSD_PARENT(psdx) = parent;
973 PSD_SYM(psdx) = sym;
974 PSD_NEXT(psdx) = 0;
975 PSD_CHILD(psdx) = 0;
976 PSD_SLOT(psdx) = 0;
977 PSD_HASHLK(psdx) = psdhsh[val];
978 psdhsh[val] = psdx;
979 if (tpdx)
980 TLINK(tpdx) = psdx;
981 if (parent) {
982 PSD_NEXT(psdx) = PSD_CHILD(parent);
983 PSD_CHILD(parent) = psdx;
984 }
985 if (lhs) {
986 PSD_SLOT(psdx) = gpsd.nslots++;
987 } else if (type == TT_PSYM || type == TT_ISYM) {
988 if (is_source_nonlocal(psdx)) {
989 PSD_SLOT(psdx) = gpsd.nslots++;
990 }
991 }
992} /* add_psd */
993
994/*
995 * call add_psd to build a pointer source descriptor for this entry;
996 * make sure all dependent (parent) pointer source descriptors are also built.
997 */
998static void
999build_psd(int tdsx, bool lhs)
1000{
1001 int subtds;
1002 if (TLINK(tdsx))
1003 return;
1004 switch (TTYPE(tdsx)) {
1005 case TT_PSYM:
1006 add_psd(tdsx, TT_PSYM, 0, TSYM(tdsx), lhs);
1007 break;
1008 case TT_ISYM:
1009 add_psd(tdsx, TT_ISYM, 0, TSYM(tdsx), lhs);
1010 break;
1011 case TT_IND:
1012 subtds = TVAL(tdsx);
1013 build_psd(subtds, lhs);
1014 add_psd(tdsx, TT_IND, TLINK(subtds), 0, lhs);
1015 break;
1016 case TT_IIND:
1017 subtds = TVAL(tdsx);
1018 build_psd(subtds, lhs);
1019 add_psd(tdsx, TT_IIND, TLINK(subtds), 0, lhs);
1020 break;
1021 case TT_MEM:
1022 subtds = TVAL(tdsx);
1023 build_psd(subtds, lhs);
1024 add_psd(tdsx, TT_MEM, TLINK(subtds), TSYM(tdsx), lhs);
1025 break;
1026 case TT_GLOB:
1027 add_psd(tdsx, TT_GLOB, 0, 0, lhs);
1028 break;
1029 default:
1030 TLINK(tdsx) = 0;
1031 break;
1032 }
1033} /* build_psd */
1034
1035/*
1036 * find pointer source descriptor in the table
1037 */
1038static int
1039find_psd(int type, int parent, int sym)
1040{
1041 int val, psdx;
1042
1043 val = (int)((type ^ sym ^ parent) & 0x7fff) % PSDHSZ;
1044 for (psdx = psdhsh[val]; psdx > 0; psdx = PSD_HASHLK(psdx)) {
1045 if (PSD_TYPE(psdx) == type && PSD_PARENT(psdx) == parent &&
1046 PSD_SYM(psdx) == sym) {
1047 return psdx;
1048 }
1049 }
1050 return TTE_NULL;
1051} /* find_psd */

1053/*
1054 * get APTE entry, lookup in hash table
1055 */
1056static int
1057get_apte(int type, int sptr, int val, int stride)
1058{
1059 int h, aptex;
1060 h = (type * 51 + sptr + val) << 4;
1061 h = h & 0xffffff;
1062 h = h % APTEHSZ;
1063 for (aptex = aptehsh[h]; aptex; aptex = APTE_HASHLK(aptex)) {
1064 if (APTE_TYPE(aptex) == type && APTE_SPTR(aptex) == sptr &&
1065 APTE_VAL(aptex) == val
1066 && APTE_STRIDE(aptex) == stride
1067 ) {
1068 return aptex;
1069 }
1070 }
1071 aptex = STG_NEXT(apte);
1072 APTE_TYPE(aptex) = type;
1073 APTE_SPTR(aptex) = sptr;
1074 APTE_VAL(aptex) = val;
1075 APTE_MARK(aptex) = 0;
1076 APTE_STRIDE(aptex) = stride;
1077 APTE_HASHLK(aptex) = aptehsh[h];
1078 aptehsh[h] = aptex;
1079 return aptex;
1080} /* get_apte */
1081
1082/*
1083 * find but don't add APTE entry, lookup in hash table
1084 */
1085static int
1086find_apte(int type, int sptr, int val)
1087{
1088 int h, aptex;
1089 h = (type * 51 + sptr + val) << 4;
1090 h = h & 0xffffff;
1091 h = h % APTEHSZ;
1092 for (aptex = aptehsh[h]; aptex; aptex = APTE_HASHLK(aptex)) {
1093 if (APTE_TYPE(aptex) == type && APTE_SPTR(aptex) == sptr &&
1094 APTE_VAL(aptex) == val) {
1095 return aptex;
1096 }
1097 }
1098 return -1;
1099} /* find_apte */

1101/*
1102 * get new pte entry, use free list if available
1103 */
1104static int
1105get_pte(int type, int sptr, int val, int stride)
1106{
1107 int ptex;
1108 ptex = gpte.xstg_free;
1109 if (ptex > 0) {
1110 gpte.xstg_free = TPTE_NEXT(ptex);
1111 } else {
1112 ptex = STG_NEXT(gpte);
1113 }
1114 TPTE_APTEX(ptex) = get_apte(type, sptr, val, stride);
1115 TPTE_NEXT(ptex) = TTE_NULL;
1116 return ptex;
1117} /* get_pte */

1119/*
1120 * return the imprecise version of this ptetype
1121 */
1122static int
1123imprecise_ptetype(int ptetype)
1124{
1125 if (ptetype == TT_PSYM)
1126 ptetype = TT_ISYM;
1127 else if (ptetype == TT_GDYN)
1128 ptetype = TT_IGDYN;
1129 else if (ptetype == TT_LDYN)
1130 ptetype = TT_ILDYN;
1131 else if (ptetype == TT_IND)
1132 ptetype = TT_IIND;
1133 return ptetype;
1134} /* imprecise_ptetype */

1136/*
1137 * copy pte tree
1138 */
1139static int
1140copy_pte(int ptex, int imprecise, int mstride)
1141{
1142 int newptex, ptetype;
1143 ptetype = TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(ptex));
1144 if (imprecise)
1145 ptetype = imprecise_ptetype(ptetype);
1146 newptex = get_pte(ptetype, TPTE_SPTR(ptex), TPTE_VAL(ptex),
1147 TPTE_STRIDE(ptex) * mstride
1148 );
1149 switch (TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(newptex))) {
1150 case TT_IND:
1151 case TT_IIND:
1152 case TT_MEM:
1153 TPTE_VAL(newptex) = copy_pte(TPTE_VAL(ptex), imprecise, 0);
1154 break;
1155 }
1156 return newptex;
1157} /* copy_pte */

1159/*
1160 * free a single pte
1161 */
1162static void
1163free_pte(int ptex)
1164{
1165
1166 switch (TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(ptex))) {
1167 case TT_IND:
1168 case TT_IIND:
1169 case TT_MEM:
1170 free_pte(TPTE_VAL(ptex));
1171 break;
1172 }
1173 TPTE_APTEX(ptex) = 0;
1174 TPTE_NEXT(ptex) = gpte.xstg_free;
1175 gpte.xstg_free = ptex;
1176} /* free_pte */

1178/*
1179 * clear the TPTE list at LHEAD(sl)
1180 */
1181static void
1182free_list(int ptelistx)
1183{
1184 int ptex, nextptex;
1185 nextptex = ptelistx;
1186 for (ptex = nextptex; ptex > 0; ptex = nextptex) {
1187 nextptex = TPTE_NEXT(ptex);
1188 free_pte(ptex);
1189 }
1190} /* free_list */

1202/*
1203 * reverse depth first ordering, and rdfo number for each node
1204 */
1205static int rdfocount, *rdfo, *rdfonum;
1206#if DEBUG
1207#define RDFO(r) \
1208 rdfo[r >= 0 && r <= opt.num_nodes ? r : (interr("bad RDFO index", r, 4), 0)]
1209#define RDFONUM(r) \
1210 rdfonum[r >= 0 && r <= opt.num_nodes \
1211 ? r \
1212 : (interr("bad RDFONUM index", r, 4), 0)]
1213#else
1214#define RDFO(r) rdfo[r]
1215#define RDFONUM(r) rdfonum[r]
1216#endif
1217
1218/*
1219 * v is a flow graph number; build reverse-depth-first order
1220 * of flow graph nodes
1221 */
1222static void
1223buildrdfo(int v)
1224{
1225 PSI_P s;
1226 int sv;
1227 RDFONUM(v) = -1;
1228 for (s = FG_SUCC(v); s != PSI_P_NULL; s = PSI_NEXT(s)) {
1229 sv = PSI_NODE(s);
1230 if (RDFONUM(sv) == 0) {
1231 buildrdfo(sv);
1232 }
1233 }
1234 ++rdfocount;
1235 RDFO(rdfocount) = v;
1236 RDFONUM(v) = rdfocount;
1237} /* buildrdfo */

1239static int
1240make_address(int astx, int pt, int sym, int offset)
1241{
1242 int tdsx;
1243 if (pt == TT_UNK)
1244 return 0;
1245 tdsx = STG_NEXT(gtpd);
1246 TTYPE(tdsx) = pt;
1247 TSYM(tdsx) = sym;
1248 TVAL(tdsx) = offset;
1249 return tdsx;
1250} /* make_address */

1252/*
1253 * fill in temporary pointer structure descriptors
1254 */
1255static int
1256make_address_for_ast(int astx, int parentast)
1257{
1258 int a, sptr, ttype, ret;
1259 ttype = TT_PSYM;
1260 a = astx;
1261 sptr = 0;
1262 while (!sptr) {
1263 switch (A_TYPEG(a)) {
1264 case A_ID:
1265 sptr = A_SPTRG(a);
1266 break;
1267 case A_MEM:
1268 if (parentast && A_TKNG(parentast) == TK_ALLOCATE &&
1269 A_SPTRG(A_MEMG(a)) && DTY(DTYPEG(A_SPTRG(A_MEMG(a)))) == TY_ARRAY) {
1270 /* process allocate of an array that is a structure member */
1271 sptr = A_SPTRG(A_MEMG(a));
1272 }
1273 a = A_PARENTG(a);
1274 ttype = TT_ISYM;
1275 break;
1276 case A_SUBSCR:
1277 a = A_LOPG(a);
1278 ttype = TT_ISYM;
1279 break;
1280 default:
1281 sptr = -1;
1282 break;
1283 }
1284 }
1285 if (sptr > 0) {
1286 ret = make_address(astx, ttype, sptr, 0);
1287 } else {
1288 ret = make_address(astx, TT_UNK, 0, 0);
1289 }
1290 return ret;
1291} /* make_address_for_ast */

1293/*
1294 * get ptr source descriptor of LHS
1295 * decide if RHS is a real pointer target or indirect through pointer source
1296 * create pseudo assignment to represent all this
1297 * stride is only used for F90
1298 */
1299static void
1300make_assignment(int v, int iltx, int lhstds, int rhstds, int add, int stride)
1301{
1302 int lhspsdx, asx, rhsptex, rhspsdx;
1303#if DEBUG
1304 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
1305 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "node:%d bih:%d ilt:%d lhs:%d <= rhs:%d ", v,
1306 FG_TO_BIH(v), iltx, lhstds, rhstds);
1307 puttds(lhstds);
1308 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, " <= ");
1309 puttds(rhstds);
1310 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "\n");
1311 printast(iltx);
1312 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, " (stride=%d)\n", stride);
1313 }
1314#endif
1315 build_psd(lhstds, true);
1316 lhspsdx = TLINK(lhstds);
1317 asx = 0;
1318 switch (TTYPE(rhstds)) {
1319 case TT_PSYM:
1320 case TT_ISYM:
1321 /* real pointer target */
1322 rhsptex = get_pte(TTYPE(rhstds), TSYM(rhstds), 0,
1323 stride
1324 );
1325
1326 asx = STG_NEXT(as);
1327 ASTYPE(asx) = add ? AS_ADD_DIRECT : AS_DIRECT;
1328 ASLHS(asx) = lhspsdx;
1329 ASRHS(asx) = rhsptex;
1330 ASNODE(asx) = v;
1331 ASILT(asx) = iltx;
1332 ASNEXT(asx) = 0;
1333 ASSTRIDE(asx) = stride;
1334 break;
1335
1336 case TT_CON:
1337 case TT_GDYN:
1338 case TT_IGDYN:
1339 case TT_LDYN:
1340 case TT_ILDYN:
1341 /* real pointer target */
1342 rhsptex = get_pte(TTYPE(rhstds), TSYM(rhstds), TVAL(rhstds),
1343 stride
1344 );
1345
1346 asx = STG_NEXT(as);
1347 ASTYPE(asx) = add ? AS_ADD_DIRECT : AS_DIRECT;
1348 ASLHS(asx) = lhspsdx;
1349 ASRHS(asx) = rhsptex;
1350 ASNODE(asx) = v;
1351 ASILT(asx) = iltx;
1352 ASNEXT(asx) = 0;
1353 ASSTRIDE(asx) = stride;
1354 break;
1355 case TT_UNK:
1356 asx = STG_NEXT(as);
1357 ASTYPE(asx) = AS_UNK;
1358 ASLHS(asx) = lhspsdx;
1359 ASRHS(asx) = 0;
1360 ASNODE(asx) = v;
1361 ASILT(asx) = iltx;
1362 ASNEXT(asx) = 0;
1363 ASSTRIDE(asx) = stride;
1364 break;
1365 case TT_UNINIT:
1366 asx = STG_NEXT(as);
1367 ASTYPE(asx) = AS_UNINIT;
1368 ASLHS(asx) = lhspsdx;
1369 ASRHS(asx) = 0;
1370 ASNODE(asx) = v;
1371 ASILT(asx) = iltx;
1372 ASNEXT(asx) = 0;
1373 ASSTRIDE(asx) = stride;
1374 break;
1375 default:
1376 /* indirect or otherwise; need dataflow analysis */
1377 build_psd(rhstds, false);
1378 rhspsdx = TLINK(rhstds);
1379
1380 asx = STG_NEXT(as);
1381 ASTYPE(asx) = add ? AS_ADD_INDIRECT : AS_INDIRECT;
1382 ASLHS(asx) = lhspsdx;
1383 ASRHS(asx) = rhspsdx;
1384 ASNODE(asx) = v;
1385 ASILT(asx) = iltx;
1386 ASNEXT(asx) = 0;
1387 ASSTRIDE(asx) = stride;
1388 break;
1389 }
1390 if (asx) {
1391 if (prevasx) {
1392 ASNEXT(prevasx) = asx;
1393 } else {
1394 FIRSTAS(v) = asx;
1395 }
1396 prevasx = asx;
1397 }
1398#if DEBUG
1399 if (asx && DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
1400 putassign(asx);
1401 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "\n");
1402 }
1403#endif
1404} /* make_assignment */
1405
1406/*
1407 * Find the stride of the leftmost dimension of this pointer target reference
1408 * Return zero if it's not a constant.
1409 */
1410static int
1411find_stride(int astx)
1412{
1413 if (A_TYPEG(astx) == A_ID) {
1414 /* pointer points to whole array */
1415 return 1;
1416 } else if (A_TYPEG(astx) == A_SUBSCR) {
1417 /* find stride of leftmost subscript */
1418 int asd, astss, sptr;
1419 asd = A_ASDG(astx);
1420 astss = ASD_SUBS(asd, 0);
1421 if (A_TYPEG(astss) != A_TRIPLE) {
1422 return 0;
1423 }
1424 astss = A_STRIDEG(astss);
1425 if (astss == 0)
1426 return 1;
1427 if (!A_ALIASG(astss))
1428 return 0;
1429 astss = A_ALIASG(astss);
1430 if (A_TYPEG(astss) != A_CNST)
1431 return 0;
1432 sptr = A_SPTRG(astss);
1433 switch (DTY(DTYPEG(sptr))) {
1434 case TY_INT8:
1435 case TY_INT:
1436 case TY_SINT:
1437 case TY_BINT:
1438 if (CONVAL1G(sptr) != 0)
1439 return 0;
1440 return CONVAL2G(sptr);
1441 default:
1442 return 0;
1443 }
1444 } else {
1445 return 0;
1446 }
1447} /* find_stride */
1448
1449/*
1450 * find pointer assignments
1451 * characterize both LHS and RHS as pointer source descriptors
1452 * this must also handle other assignments that change pointers
1453 * and treat them as unknown assignments
1454 * as well as function calls with pointer arguments
1455 */
1456static int globalv;
1457
1458static void
1459_find_pointer_assignments_f90(int astx, int *pstdx)
1460{
1461 int lop, allglobals, allargs, dpdsc, funcsptr;
1462 int dummy, args, argcnt, a, arg, argsptr;
1463 switch (A_TYPEG(astx)) {
1464 case A_ICALL:
1465 /* intrinsic call, see if it is ptr assignment */
1466 if (A_OPTYPEG(astx) == I_PTR2_ASSIGN) {
1467 /* pointer assignment */
1468 int args, lhsastx, rhsastx, lhsdsx, rhsdsx, stride;
1469 args = A_ARGSG(astx);
1470 lhsastx = ARGT_ARG(args, 0);
1471 rhsastx = ARGT_ARG(args, 1);
1472 lhsdsx = make_address_for_ast(lhsastx, astx);
1473 rhsdsx = make_address_for_ast(rhsastx, astx);
1474 stride = find_stride(rhsastx);
1475 make_assignment(globalv, *pstdx, lhsdsx, rhsdsx, 0, stride);
1476 } else if (A_OPTYPEG(astx) == I_NULLIFY) {
1477 /* pointer nullify */
1478 int args, lhsastx, lhsdsx, rhsdsx;
1479 args = A_ARGSG(astx);
1480 lhsastx = ARGT_ARG(args, 0);
1481 lhsdsx = make_address_for_ast(lhsastx, astx);
1482 rhsdsx = make_address(astx, TT_CON, 0, 0);
1483 make_assignment(globalv, *pstdx, lhsdsx, rhsdsx, 0, 0);
1484 }
1485 break;
1486 case A_CALL:
1487 lop = A_LOPG(astx);
1488 allglobals = 1;
1489 allargs = 0;
1490 if (A_TYPEG(lop) == A_ID) {
1491 funcsptr = A_SPTRG(lop);
1492 dpdsc = DPDSCG(funcsptr);
1493 if (DPDSCG(funcsptr)) {
1494 allargs = 1; /* all pointer dummy args might be modified */
1495 }
1496 }
1497 if (allglobals) {
1498 make_assignment(globalv, *pstdx, 2, 0, 0, 0);
1499 }
1500 if (allargs) {
1501 /* have funcsptr, dpdsc */
1502 args = A_ARGSG(astx);
1503 argcnt = A_ARGCNTG(astx);
1504 for (a = 0; a < argcnt; ++a) {
1505 arg = ARGT_ARG(args, a);
1506 if (A_TYPEG(arg) == A_ID) {
1507 argsptr = A_SPTRG(arg);
1508 if (POINTERG(argsptr)) {
1509 int lhsdsx, rhsdsx;
1510 /* if the pointer might otherwise be modified */
1511 dummy = aux.dpdsc_base[dpdsc + a];
1512 if (dummy && POINTERG(dummy)) {
1513 /* yes, it might */
1514 lhsdsx = make_address_for_ast(arg, astx);
1515 rhsdsx = make_address(astx, TT_UNK, 0, 0);
1516 make_assignment(globalv, *pstdx, lhsdsx, rhsdsx, 0, 0);
1517 }
1518 }
1519 }
1520 }
1521 }
1522 break;
1523 case A_ALLOC:
1524 /* allocate/deallocate */
1525 if (A_TKNG(astx) == TK_ALLOCATE) {
1526 /* allocate */
1527 int objastx, lhsdsx, rhsdsx;
1528 objastx = A_SRCG(astx);
1529 if (A_TYPEG(objastx) == A_SUBSCR) {
1530 objastx = A_LOPG(objastx);
1531 }
1532 lhsdsx = make_address_for_ast(objastx, astx);
1533 rhsdsx = make_address(astx, TT_LDYN, 0, gdyn.local_dyn++);
1534 make_assignment(globalv, *pstdx, lhsdsx, rhsdsx, 0, 1);
1535 } else {
1536 /* deallocate */
1537 int objastx, lhsdsx, rhsdsx;
1538 objastx = A_SRCG(astx);
1539 if (A_TYPEG(objastx) == A_SUBSCR) {
1540 objastx = A_LOPG(objastx);
1541 }
1542 lhsdsx = make_address_for_ast(objastx, astx);
1543 rhsdsx = make_address(astx, TT_CON, 0, 0);
1544 make_assignment(globalv, *pstdx, lhsdsx, rhsdsx, 0, 0);
1545 }
1546 break;
1547 }
1548} /* _find_pointer_assignments_f90 */
1549
1550/*
1551 * symbolically interpret the statements in this statement
1552 * represent the pointer target information as a TPTE list
1553 */
1554static void
1555find_pointer_assignments_f90(int stdx)
1556{
1557 prevasx = 0;
1558 gtpd.stg_avail = 3;
1559 ast_visit(1, 1);
1560 globalv = stdx;
1561 ast_traverse(STD_AST(stdx), NULL, _find_pointer_assignments_f90, &stdx);
1562 ast_unvisit();
1563} /* find_pointer_assignments_f90 */

1602/*
1603 * Add pseudo assignments for initial pointer information at the program entry
1604 */
1605static void
1606make_init_assignment(int v, int sourcesptr, int stars, int targettype,
1607 int targetinfo)
1608{
1609 int lhspsdx, asx, rhsptex;
1610 int lhstds;
1611 /* get LHS tds for source */
1612 Trace(("init assignment node %d sourcesptr %d stars=%d targettype=%d "
1613 "targetinfo=%d",
1614 v, sourcesptr, stars, targettype, targetinfo));
1615 lhstds = make_address(0, TT_PSYM, sourcesptr, 0);
1616 while (stars-- > 0) {
1617 lhstds = make_address(0, TT_IND, 0, lhstds);
1618 }
1619 build_psd(lhstds, true);
1620 lhspsdx = TLINK(lhstds);
1621 asx = 0;
1622 /* get PTE for RHS */
1623 switch (targettype) {
1624 case 1:
1625 /* another SPTR */
1626 rhsptex = get_pte(TT_ISYM, targetinfo, 0, 0);
1627 asx = STG_NEXT(as);
1628 ASTYPE(asx) = AS_INIT;
1629 ASLHS(asx) = lhspsdx;
1630 ASRHS(asx) = rhsptex;
1631 ASNODE(asx) = v;
1632 ASILT(asx) = 0;
1633 ASNEXT(asx) = 0;
1634 break;
1635 case 2:
1636 /* anonymous variable */
1637 rhsptex = get_pte(TT_ANON, 0, anonymous_number(targetinfo), 0);
1638 asx = STG_NEXT(as);
1639 ASTYPE(asx) = AS_INIT;
1640 ASLHS(asx) = lhspsdx;
1641 ASRHS(asx) = rhsptex;
1642 ASNODE(asx) = v;
1643 ASILT(asx) = 0;
1644 ASNEXT(asx) = 0;
1645 break;
1646 case 3:
1647 /* allocatable storage */
1648 rhsptex = get_pte(TT_GDYN, 0, dynamic_number(targetinfo), 0);
1649 asx = STG_NEXT(as);
1650 ASTYPE(asx) = AS_INIT;
1651 ASLHS(asx) = lhspsdx;
1652 ASRHS(asx) = rhsptex;
1653 ASNODE(asx) = v;
1654 ASILT(asx) = 0;
1655 ASNEXT(asx) = 0;
1656 break;
1657 default:
1658 interr("bad target type", targettype, ERR_Fatal);
1659 return;
1660 }
1661 if (asx) {
1662 ASNEXT(asx) = FIRSTAS(v);
1663 FIRSTAS(v) = asx;
1664 }
1665} /* make_init_assignment */

1668/*
1669 * add the TPTE at ptex to the TPTE list at LHEAD(s)
1670 */
1671static void
1672add_list(int ptex, int psdx, int imprecise, int mstride)
1673{
1674 int newptex;
1675 newptex = copy_pte(ptex, imprecise, mstride);
1676 TPTE_NEXT(newptex) = LHEAD(PSD_SLOT(psdx));
1677 LHEAD(PSD_SLOT(psdx)) = newptex;
1678} /* add_list */

1680/*
1681 * copy the TPTE list at T to the TPTE list at position LHEAD(s)
1682 */
1683static int
1684copy_list(int ptelistx)
1685{
1686 int ptex, newptex, headptex;
1687 if (ptelistx == TPTE_UNK) {
1688 return TPTE_UNK;
1689 } else {
1690 headptex = TTE_NULL;
1691 for (ptex = ptelistx; ptex > 0; ptex = TPTE_NEXT(ptex)) {
1692 newptex = copy_pte(ptex, 0, 1);
1693 TPTE_NEXT(newptex) = headptex;
1694 headptex = newptex;
1695 }
1696 return headptex;
1697 }
1698} /* copy_list */

1700/*

1702 */

1704unk_all(void)
1705{

1707 for (sl = 1; sl < gpsd.nslots; ++sl) {
1708 free_list_slot(sl);

1713/*
1714 * clear all information for globals, or anything that might point to a global
1715 */
1716static void
1717unk_globals(void)
1718{

1720 for (sl = 1; sl < gpsd.nslots; ++sl) {
1721 if (is_source_global(SLOT(sl)) && !safe_symbol(SLOT(sl))) {
1722 free_list_slot(sl);
1723 LHEAD(sl) = TPTE_UNK;
1724 }
1725 }
1726} /* unk_globals */

1728/*
1729 * set up the APTE flags
1730 * mark any APTE that might be a target of the given psd
1731 * we're looking for the case
1732 * p = &q;
1733 * q = &a;
1734 * so we have to add &a to the target list of *p as well.
1735 */
1736static unsigned int marker = 0;
1737static unsigned int unknown_mark = 0, nonlocal_mark = 0, some_nonlocal_mark = 0;
1738static void
1739mark_apte_targets(int psdx)
1740{
1741 int parentpsdx, parentsl, ptex, sptr, aptex;
1742 ++marker;
1743 switch (PSD_TYPE(psdx)) {
1744 case TT_PSYM:
1745 case TT_ISYM:
1746 aptex = find_apte(TT_PSYM, PSD_SYM(psdx), 0);
1747 if (aptex > 0)
1748 APTE_MARK(aptex) = marker;
1749 aptex = find_apte(TT_ISYM, PSD_SYM(psdx), 0);
1750 if (aptex > 0)
1751 APTE_MARK(aptex) = marker;
1752 sptr = PSD_SYM(psdx);
1753 break;
1754 case TT_IND:
1755 case TT_IIND:
1756 parentpsdx = PSD_PARENT(psdx);
1757 /* mark targets of parentpsdx */
1758 parentsl = PSD_SLOT(parentpsdx);
1759 if (LHEAD(parentsl) == TPTE_UNK) {
1760 unknown_mark = marker;
1761 } else {
1762 for (ptex = LHEAD(parentsl); ptex > 0; ptex = TPTE_NEXT(ptex)) {
1763 switch (TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(ptex))) {
1764 case TT_UNK:
1765 case TT_UNINIT:
1766 unknown_mark = marker;
1767 some_nonlocal_mark = marker;
1768 break;
1769 case TT_PSYM:
1770 case TT_ISYM:
1771 sptr = TPTE_SPTR(ptex);
1772 aptex = find_apte(TT_PSYM, sptr, 0);
1773 if (aptex > 0)
1774 APTE_MARK(aptex) = marker;
1775 aptex = find_apte(TT_ISYM, sptr, 0);
1776 if (aptex > 0)
1777 APTE_MARK(aptex) = marker;
1778 break;
1779 case TT_NLOC: /* all we know is something nonlocal, may be global */
1780 nonlocal_mark = marker;
1781 some_nonlocal_mark = marker;
1782 break;
1783 case TT_ANON: /* anonymous nonlocal */
1784 case TT_GDYN:
1785 case TT_IGDYN:
1786 case TT_LDYN:
1787 case TT_ILDYN:
1788 some_nonlocal_mark = marker;
1789 break;
1790 case TT_CON:
1791 aptex = find_apte(TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(ptex)), 0, TPTE_VAL(ptex));
1792 if (aptex > 0)
1793 APTE_MARK(aptex) = marker;
1794 break;
1795 default:
1796 /* real error */
1797 interr("bad PTE type", TPTE_TYPE(ptex), ERR_Warning);
1798 break;
1799 }
1800 }
1801 }
1802 break;
1803 case TT_MEM:
1804 /* ### */
1805 break;
1806 case TT_GLOB:
1807 case TT_NLOC:
1808 case TT_UNK:
1809 case TT_UNINIT:
1810 default:
1811 interr("bad PSD type", PSD_TYPE(psdx), ERR_Fatal);
1812 break;
1813 }
1814} /* mark_apte_targets */
1815
1816/*
1817 * return TRUE if the pointer source at psdx might
1818 * intersect with the target at targetpsdx, that is
1819 * psdx is an indirect with a parent PSD that might point to targetpsdx
1820 */
1821static int
1822might_target(int psdx)
1823{
1824 int parentpsdx, parentsl, ptex, sptr, aptex;
1825 switch (PSD_TYPE(psdx)) {
1826 case TT_IND:
1827 case TT_IIND:
1828 /* see if the parent might point to the lhs;
1829 * changing the lhs changes the parent pointee, which is this */
1830 parentpsdx = PSD_PARENT(psdx);
1831 parentsl = PSD_SLOT(parentpsdx);
1832 if (LHEAD(parentsl) == TPTE_UNK)
1833 return TRUE;
1834 if (unknown_mark == marker)
1835 return TRUE;
1836 for (ptex = LHEAD(parentsl); ptex > 0; ptex = TPTE_NEXT(ptex)) {
1837 switch (TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(ptex))) {
1838 case TT_UNK:
1839 case TT_UNINIT:
1840 return TRUE;
1841 case TT_PSYM:
1842 case TT_ISYM:
1843 aptex = TPTE_APTEX(ptex);
1844 if (APTE_MARK(aptex) == marker)
1845 return TRUE;
1846 break;
1847 case TT_NLOC: /* all we know is something nonlocal, may be global */
1848 if (some_nonlocal_mark == marker)
1849 return TRUE;
1850 break;
1851 case TT_ANON: /* anonymous nonlocal */
1852 case TT_GDYN:
1853 case TT_IGDYN:
1854 case TT_LDYN:
1855 case TT_ILDYN:
1856 case TT_CON:
1857 aptex = TPTE_APTEX(ptex);
1858 if (APTE_MARK(aptex) == marker)
1859 return TRUE;
1860 break;
1861 default:
1862 /* real error */
1863 interr("bad PTE type", TPTE_TYPE(ptex), ERR_Warning);
1864 return TRUE;
1865 }
1866 }
1867 break;
1868 case TT_ISYM:
1869 case TT_PSYM:
1870 aptex = find_apte(TT_PSYM, PSD_SYM(psdx), 0);
1871 if (aptex > 0 && APTE_MARK(aptex) == marker)
1872 return TRUE;
1873 aptex = find_apte(TT_ISYM, PSD_SYM(psdx), 0);
1874 if (aptex > 0 && APTE_MARK(aptex) == marker)
1875 return TRUE;
1876 sptr = PSD_SYM(psdx);
1877 break;
1878 /* ignore the other types, which don't / can't point to the LHS */
1879 }
1880 return FALSE;
1881} /* might_target */
1882
1883static int CHANGES;
1884
1885/*
1886 * Check all the pte's in the list for the lhs
1887 * if the lhs target list is unknown, stop here
1888 * if the pte is 'unknown', change lhs target list to unknown, increment
1889 * CHANGES, stop
1890 * if there is a match, stop here, no changes
1891 * if there is a less precise one match, stop here, no changes
1892 * if there is a more precise one, make it less precise, increment CHANGES, stop
1893 * here
1894 * otherwise, add this pte to the list, increment CHANGES
1895 * stride is only used for F90
1896 */
1897static void
1898_addtpte(int lhspsdx, int ptex, int imprecise, int mstride)
1899{
1900 int ptetype, lpte, lptetype, ptes, ptestype, lptes, lptestype, match, sl;
1901 int rhspsdx, rsl;
1902 sl = PSD_SLOT(lhspsdx);
1903 if (LHEAD(sl) == TPTE_UNK)
1904 return;
1905 if (ptex == TPTE_UNK) {
1906 ++CHANGES;
1907 free_list_slot(sl);
1908 LHEAD(sl) = TPTE_UNK;
1909 return;
1910 }
1911 ptetype = TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(ptex));
1912 if (imprecise)
1913 ptetype = imprecise_ptetype(ptetype);
1914 /* in PGF90, we can't have a pointer to a pointer.
1915 * p => b where b is a pointer or allocatable means make p
1916 * point to what b points to */
1917 if ((ptetype == TT_PSYM || ptetype == TT_ISYM) && TPTE_SPTR(ptex) &&
1918 (POINTERG(TPTE_SPTR(ptex)) || ALLOCATTRG(TPTE_SPTR(ptex)))) {
1919 /* get the RHS PSD entry */
1920 rhspsdx = find_psd(TT_PSYM, 0, TPTE_SPTR(ptex));
1921 /* if p => a, and a is a pointer or allocatable, then p can point to
1922 * anything that a can point to */
1923 if (rhspsdx <= 0) {
1924 _addtpte(lhspsdx, TPTE_UNK, 0, 0);
1925 } else {
1926 int rptex, imp;
1927 rsl = PSD_SLOT(rhspsdx);
1928 if (rsl) {
1929 imp = 0;
1930 if (ptetype == TT_ISYM || imprecise_ptetype(ptetype) == ptetype)
1931 imp = 1;
1932 for (rptex = LHEAD(rsl); rptex > 0; rptex = TPTE_NEXT(rptex)) {
1933 _addtpte(lhspsdx, rptex, imp, TPTE_STRIDE(ptex));
1934 }
1935 }
1936 }
1937 return;
1938 }
1939 match = 0;
1940 for (lpte = LHEAD(sl); lpte > 0; lpte = TPTE_NEXT(lpte)) {
1941 lptetype = TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(lpte));
1942 if (imprecise)
1943 lptetype = imprecise_ptetype(lptetype);
1944 if (lptetype == ptetype && TPTE_SPTR(lpte) == TPTE_SPTR(ptex) &&
1945 TPTE_VAL(lpte) == TPTE_VAL(ptex)
1946 && TPTE_STRIDE(lpte) * mstride == TPTE_STRIDE(lpte)
1947 ) {
1948 return;
1949 }
1950 /* see if this is indirection from the same symbol */
1951 match = 1;
1952 for (lptes = lpte, ptes = ptex; lptes > 0 && ptes > 0;
1953 lptes = TPTE_VAL(lptes), ptes = TPTE_VAL(ptes)) {
1954 lptestype = TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(lptes));
1955 if (imprecise)
1956 lptestype = imprecise_ptetype(lptestype);
1957 ptestype = TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(ptes));
1958 if (TPTE_STRIDE(lpte) * mstride != TPTE_STRIDE(lpte)) {
1959 match = 0;
1960 break;
1961 }
1962 if (lptestype == TT_IND || lptestype == TT_IIND) {
1963 if (ptestype != TT_IND && ptestype != TT_IIND) {
1964 match = 0;
1965 break;
1966 } else if (TPTE_SPTR(ptes) != TPTE_SPTR(lptes)) {
1967 match = 0;
1968 break;
1969 }
1970 } else if (lptestype == TT_PSYM || lptestype == TT_ISYM) {
1971 if (ptestype != TT_PSYM && ptestype != TT_ISYM) {
1972 match = 0;
1973 break;
1974 } else if (TPTE_SPTR(ptes) != TPTE_SPTR(lptes)) {
1975 match = 0;
1976 break;
1977 }
1978 } else if (lptestype == TT_GDYN || lptestype == TT_IGDYN) {
1979 if (ptestype != TT_GDYN && ptestype != TT_IGDYN) {
1980 match = 0;
1981 break;
1982 } else if (TPTE_VAL(ptes) != TPTE_VAL(lptes)) {
1983 match = 0;
1984 break;
1985 }
1986 break;
1987 } else if (lptestype == TT_LDYN || lptestype == TT_ILDYN) {
1988 if (ptestype != TT_LDYN && ptestype != TT_ILDYN) {
1989 match = 0;
1990 break;
1991 } else if (TPTE_VAL(ptes) != TPTE_VAL(lptes)) {
1992 match = 0;
1993 break;
1994 }
1995 break;
1996 } else {
1997 match = 0;
1998 break;
1999 }
2000 }
2001 if (match) {
2002 /* change lptes to the more imprecise of lptes and ptex, and be done with
2003 * it */
2004 for (lptes = lpte, ptes = ptex; lptes > 0 && ptes > 0;
2005 lptes = TPTE_VAL(lptes), ptes = TPTE_VAL(ptes)) {
2006 lptestype = TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(lptes));
2007 if (imprecise)
2008 lptestype = imprecise_ptetype(lptestype);
2009 ptestype = TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(ptes));
2010 if (ptestype == TT_IIND) {
2011 if (lptestype == TT_IND) {
2012 TPTE_APTEX(lptes) =
2013 get_apte(TT_IIND, TPTE_SPTR(lptes), TPTE_VAL(lptes),
2014 TPTE_STRIDE(lptes) * mstride
2015 );
2016 ++CHANGES;
2017 }
2018 /* loop */
2019 } else if (ptestype == TT_IND) {
2020 /* loop */
2021 } else if (ptestype == TT_ISYM) {
2022 if (lptestype == TT_PSYM) {
2023 TPTE_APTEX(lptes) =
2024 get_apte(TT_ISYM, TPTE_SPTR(lptes), TPTE_VAL(lptes),
2025 TPTE_STRIDE(lptes) * mstride
2026 );
2027 ++CHANGES;
2028 }
2029 break;
2030 } else if (ptestype == TT_PSYM) {
2031 break;
2032 } else if (ptestype == TT_IGDYN) {
2033 if (lptestype == TT_GDYN) {
2034 TPTE_APTEX(lptes) =
2035 get_apte(TT_IGDYN, TPTE_SPTR(lptes), TPTE_VAL(lptes),
2036 TPTE_STRIDE(lptes) * mstride
2037 );
2038 ++CHANGES;
2039 }
2040 break;
2041 } else if (ptestype == TT_GDYN) {
2042 break;
2043 } else if (ptestype == TT_ILDYN) {
2044 if (lptestype == TT_LDYN) {
2045 TPTE_APTEX(lptes) =
2046 get_apte(TT_ILDYN, TPTE_SPTR(lptes), TPTE_VAL(lptes),
2047 TPTE_STRIDE(lptes) * mstride
2048 );
2049 ++CHANGES;
2050 }
2051 break;
2052 } else if (ptestype == TT_LDYN) {
2053 break;
2054 } else {
2055 break;
2056 }
2057 }
2058 }
2059 }
2060 if (!match) {
2061 /* no match found, add */
2062 ++CHANGES;
2063 add_list(ptex, lhspsdx, imprecise, mstride);
2064 }
2065
2066} /* _addtpte */
2067
2068static void
2069addtpte(int lhspsdx, int ptex)
2070{
2071 int sl;
2072 _addtpte(lhspsdx, ptex, 0, 1);
2073 /* pointers that might target lhs must be modified as well */
2074 mark_apte_targets(lhspsdx);
2075 for (sl = 1; sl < gpsd.nslots; ++sl) {
2076 if (SLOT(sl) != lhspsdx && might_target(SLOT(sl))) {
2077 _addtpte(SLOT(sl), ptex, 1, 0);
2078 }
2079 }
2080} /* addtpte */
2081
2082static void
2083inittpte(int lhspsdx, int ptex)
2084{
2085 _addtpte(lhspsdx, ptex, 0, 1);
2086} /* inittpte */
2087
2088/*
2089 * remove the target information for the LHS
2090 * add the single target from the RHS
2091 * must modify *LHS to match *RHS
2092 * anything that can point to LHS must also be modified
2093 */
2094static void
2095replacepte(int lhspsdx, int ptex)
2096{
2097 free_list_slot(PSD_SLOT(lhspsdx));
2098 addtpte(lhspsdx, ptex);
2099} /* replacepte */
2100
2101static void
2102add_tptelist(int lhspsdx, int ptelistx)
2103{
2104 int ptex, sl;
2105 if (ptelistx == TPTE_UNK) {
2106 _addtpte(lhspsdx, ptelistx, 1, 1);
2107 /* pointers that might target lhs must be modified as well */
2108 mark_apte_targets(lhspsdx);
2109 for (sl = 1; sl < gpsd.nslots; ++sl) {
2110 if (SLOT(sl) != lhspsdx && might_target(SLOT(sl))) {
2111 _addtpte(SLOT(sl), ptelistx, 1, 1);
2112 }
2113 }
2114 } else {
2115 for (ptex = ptelistx; ptex > 0; ptex = TPTE_NEXT(ptex)) {
2116 _addtpte(lhspsdx, ptex, 0, 1);
2117 }
2118 /* pointers that might target lhs must be modified as well */
2119 /* This is the expensive part:
2120 *
2121 * int** p1, *p2, *p3, *p4, **p5;
2122 * int a, b;
2123 *
2124 * p1 = test1 ? &p3 : &p4; -- here, p1 => p3|p4
2125 * p2 = test2 ? &a : &b; -- here, p2 => a|b
2126 *
2127 * *p1 = p2;
2128 *
2129 * We know p1 might point to p3 or p4 and p2 might point to a or b,
2130 * so we must propagage target a|b to p3 and p4 as well as **p1
2131 *
2132 * If we add the assignment
2133 * p5 = test3 ? &p3 : NULL;
2134 * before the *p1 assignment, then p5 might point to p3
2135 * we must then propagate the target a|b to *p5 as well
2136 *
2137 * So, when assigning a pointer value to *p1, any pointer target of p1
2138 * has its pointer targets updated by the pointer targets of the RHS.
2139 *
2140 * In fact, in any pointer assignment, any pointer that might alias
2141 * the LHS also has its pointer targets updated
2142 */
2143 mark_apte_targets(lhspsdx);
2144 for (sl = 1; sl < gpsd.nslots; ++sl) {
2145 if (SLOT(sl) != lhspsdx && might_target(SLOT(sl))) {
2146 for (ptex = ptelistx; ptex > 0; ptex = TPTE_NEXT(ptex)) {
2147 _addtpte(SLOT(sl), ptex, 1, 1);
2148 }
2149 }
2150 }
2151 }
2152} /* add_tptelist */
2153
2154/*
2155 * replace target information for LHS by the list
2156 */
2157static void
2158replace_tptelist(int lhspsdx, int ptelistx)
2159{
2160 free_list_slot(PSD_SLOT(lhspsdx));
2161 add_tptelist(lhspsdx, ptelistx);
2162} /* replace_tptelist */

2164/*
2165 * look at pointer targets of the LHS, add RHS targets to anything
2166 * that the LHS might point to
2167 */
2168static void
2169add_target_tptelist(int lhspsdx, int ptelistx)
2170{
2171 int sl;
2172 add_tptelist(lhspsdx, ptelistx);
2173 sl = PSD_SLOT(lhspsdx);
2174 if (LHEAD(sl) == TPTE_UNK) {
2175 /* everything changes */
2176 unk_all();
2177 }
2178} /* add_target_tptelist */

2180/*
2181 * take the RHS of the assignment, compute the effective TPTE list
2182 */
2183static int
2184effective_rhs(int psdx)
2185{
2186 int parentpsdx, sl, ptelistx, ptex;
2187 switch (PSD_TYPE(psdx)) {
2188 case TT_UNINIT:
2189 return TPTE_UNINIT;
2190
2191 case TT_UNK:
2192 /* totally unknown */
2193 return TPTE_UNK;
2194
2195 case TT_IND:
2196 /* return the list of the target */
2197 parentpsdx = PSD_PARENT(psdx);
2198 sl = PSD_SLOT(parentpsdx);
2199 if (sl == 0) {
2200 return TPTE_UNK;
2201 }
2202 return copy_list(LHEAD(sl));
2203 case TT_IIND:
2204 /* find the list of the target */
2205 parentpsdx = PSD_PARENT(psdx);
2206 sl = PSD_SLOT(parentpsdx);
2207 if (sl == 0) {
2208 return TPTE_UNK;
2209 }
2210 ptelistx = copy_list(LHEAD(sl));
2211 /* now account for the imprecision */
2212 for (ptex = ptelistx; ptex > 0; ptex = TPTE_NEXT(ptex)) {
2213 switch (TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(ptex))) {
2214 case TT_PSYM:
2215 /* make imprecise */
2216 TPTE_APTEX(ptex) = get_apte(TT_ISYM, TPTE_SPTR(ptex), TPTE_VAL(ptex),
2217 TPTE_STRIDE(ptex)
2218 );
2219 break;
2220 case TT_ISYM:
2221 /* already imprecise */
2222 break;
2223 case TT_IND:
2224 /* make imprecise */
2225 TPTE_APTEX(ptex) = get_apte(TT_IIND, TPTE_SPTR(ptex), TPTE_VAL(ptex),
2226 TPTE_STRIDE(ptex)
2227 );
2228 break;
2229 case TT_IIND:
2230 /* already imprecise */
2231 break;
2232 case TT_UNK:
2233 case TT_UNINIT:
2234 free_list(ptelistx);
2235 return TPTE_UNK;
2236 case TT_CON:
2237 free_list(ptelistx);
2238 return TPTE_UNK;
2239 }
2240 }
2241 return ptelistx;
2242 default:
2243 /* real error */
2244 interr("pointsto: unknown RHS type in assignment", PSD_TYPE(psdx), ERR_Fatal);
2245 return TPTE_UNK;
2246 }
2247} /* effective_rhs */
2248
2249/*
2250 * symbolically interpret the pointer assignments in this flow graph node
2251 * represent the pointer target information as a TPTE list
2252 */
2253static void
2254interpret(int asx)
2255{
2256 int lhspsdx, rhsptelistx, sl, stride;
2257#if DEBUG
2258 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
2259 putassign(asx);
2260 }
2261#endif
2262 stride = ASSTRIDE(asx);
2263 /* interpret assignment as changes to pointer target information */
2264 /* pointer equals address is easy, reset pointer target */
2265 /* pointer equals fetch(pointer) is easy, copy pointer targets */
2266 /* pointer equals fetch(pointer)imprecise is easy, copy pointer targets,
2267 * set imprecise */
2268 /* pointer equals unknown is easy, clear information */
2269 /* glob equals unknown is easy, clear information for all globals,
2270 * anything that might alias a global */
2271 switch (ASTYPE(asx)) {
2272 case AS_DIRECT:
2273 /* RHS must be precise or imprecise symbol. */
2274 lhspsdx = ASLHS(asx);
2275 switch (PSD_TYPE(lhspsdx)) {
2276 case TT_PSYM:
2277 /* LHS is precise symbol; this is a MUST POINTS TO relationship */
2278 replacepte(lhspsdx, ASRHS(asx));
2279 break;
2280
2281 case TT_ISYM:
2282 /* LHS is imprecise symbol; this is a MAY POINTS TO relationship */
2283 addtpte(lhspsdx, ASRHS(asx));
2284 break;
2285
2286 case TT_IND:
2287 /* LHS is indirect; MUST POINTS TO if all indirects are precise */
2288 replacepte(lhspsdx, ASRHS(asx));
2289 break;
2290 case TT_IIND:
2291 /* LHS is imprecise indirect; MAY POINTS TO */
2292 addtpte(lhspsdx, ASRHS(asx));
2293 break;
2294 case TT_GLOB:
2295 /* happens at calls. Mark all globals as unknown */
2296 unk_globals();
2297 break;
2298 case TT_UNK:
2299 case TT_UNINIT: /* should not happen */
2300 unk_all();
2301 break;
2302 case TT_MEM:
2303 /* not used yet */
2304 interr("pointsto: unknown LHS type in assignment", PSD_TYPE(lhspsdx), ERR_Warning);
2305 unk_all();
2306 break;
2307 default:
2308 /* real error */
2309 interr("pointsto: unknown LHS type in assignment", PSD_TYPE(lhspsdx), ERR_Fatal);
2310 unk_all();
2311 break;
2312 }
2313#if DEBUG
2314 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
2315 puttarget(PSD_SLOT(lhspsdx));
2316 }
2317#endif
2318 break;
2319 case AS_ADD_DIRECT:
2320 /* RHS must be precise or imprecise symbol. */
2321 lhspsdx = ASLHS(asx);
2322 switch (PSD_TYPE(lhspsdx)) {
2323 case TT_PSYM:
2324 case TT_ISYM:
2325 case TT_IND:
2326 case TT_IIND:
2327 /* LHS is imprecise indirect; MAY POINTS TO */
2328 addtpte(lhspsdx, ASRHS(asx));
2329 break;
2330 case TT_GLOB:
2331 /* happens at calls. Mark all globals as unknown */
2332 unk_globals();
2333 break;
2334 case TT_UNK:
2335 case TT_UNINIT: /* should not happen */
2336 unk_all();
2337 break;
2338 case TT_MEM:
2339 /* not used yet */
2340 interr("pointsto: unknown LHS type in assignment", PSD_TYPE(lhspsdx), ERR_Warning);
2341 unk_all();
2342 break;
2343 default:
2344 /* real error */
2345 interr("pointsto: unknown LHS type in assignment", PSD_TYPE(lhspsdx), ERR_Fatal);
2346 unk_all();
2347 break;
2348 }
2349#if DEBUG
2350 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
2351 puttarget(PSD_SLOT(lhspsdx));
2352 }
2353#endif
2354 break;
2355 case AS_INIT:
2356 /* RHS must be precise or imprecise symbol. */
2357 lhspsdx = ASLHS(asx);
2358 sl = PSD_SLOT(lhspsdx);
2359 if (LHEAD(sl) == TPTE_UNK) {
2360 free_list_slot(sl);
2361 }
2362 switch (PSD_TYPE(lhspsdx)) {
2363 case TT_PSYM:
2364 /* LHS is precise symbol; this is a MUST POINTS TO relationship */
2365 inittpte(lhspsdx, ASRHS(asx));
2366 break;
2367
2368 case TT_ISYM:
2369 /* LHS is imprecise symbol; this is a MAY POINTS TO relationship */
2370 inittpte(lhspsdx, ASRHS(asx));
2371 break;
2372
2373 case TT_IND:
2374 /* LHS is indirect; MUST POINTS TO if all indirects are precise */
2375 inittpte(lhspsdx, ASRHS(asx));
2376 break;
2377 case TT_IIND:
2378 /* LHS is imprecise indirect; MAY POINTS TO */
2379 inittpte(lhspsdx, ASRHS(asx));
2380 break;
2381 case TT_UNK:
2382 case TT_UNINIT: /* should not happen */
2383 unk_all();
2384 break;
2385 case TT_MEM:
2386 /* not used yet */
2387 interr("pointsto: unknown LHS type in init assignment", PSD_TYPE(lhspsdx),
2388 2);
2389 unk_all();
2390 break;
2391 default:
2392 /* real error */
2393 interr("pointsto: unknown LHS type in init assignment", PSD_TYPE(lhspsdx),
2394 4);
2395 break;
2396 }
2397#if DEBUG
2398 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
2399 puttarget(PSD_SLOT(lhspsdx));
2400 }
2401#endif
2402 break;
2403 case AS_INDIRECT:
2404 /* Get the effect of the RHS */
2405 rhsptelistx = effective_rhs(ASRHS(asx));
2406#if DEBUG
2407 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
2408 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, " effective target --> ");
2409 putptelist(rhsptelistx);
2410 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "\n");
2411 }
2412#endif
2413 lhspsdx = ASLHS(asx);
2414 switch (PSD_TYPE(lhspsdx)) {
2415 case TT_PSYM:
2416 /* LHS is precise symbol; this is a MUST POINTS TO relationship */
2417 replace_tptelist(lhspsdx, rhsptelistx);
2418 break;
2419
2420 case TT_ISYM:
2421 /* LHS is imprecise symbol; this is a MAY POINTS TO relationship */
2422 add_tptelist(lhspsdx, rhsptelistx);
2423 break;
2424
2425 case TT_GLOB:
2426 /* this is used when globals might be modified */
2427 replace_tptelist(lhspsdx, rhsptelistx);
2428 /* must also modify target list for any global pointer source */
2429 for (sl = 1; sl < gpsd.nslots; ++sl) {
2430 if (is_source_global(SLOT(sl))) {
2431 add_tptelist(SLOT(sl), rhsptelistx);
2432 }
2433 }
2434 break;
2435
2436 case TT_IND:
2437 case TT_IIND:
2438 /* need to handle this */
2439 add_target_tptelist(lhspsdx, rhsptelistx);
2440 Trace(("indirect LHS type in assignment"));
2441 break;
2442 case TT_UNK:
2443 case TT_UNINIT: /* should not happen */
2444 unk_all();
2445 break;
2446 case TT_MEM:
2447 /* ### really want to handle member LHS types */
2448 interr("pointsto: unknown LHS type in assignment", PSD_TYPE(lhspsdx), ERR_Warning);
2449 Trace(("unknown LHS type in assignment"));
2450 break;
2451 default:
2452 /* real error */
2453 interr("pointsto: unknown LHS type in assignment", PSD_TYPE(lhspsdx), ERR_Fatal);
2454 Trace(("unknown LHS type in assignment"));
2455 break;
2456 }
2457#if DEBUG
2458 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
2459 puttarget(PSD_SLOT(lhspsdx));
2460 }
2461#endif
2462 free_list(rhsptelistx);
2463 break;
2464 case AS_ADD_INDIRECT:
2465 /* Get the effect of the RHS */
2466 rhsptelistx = effective_rhs(ASRHS(asx));
2467#if DEBUG
2468 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
2469 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, " effective target --> ");
2470 putptelist(rhsptelistx);
2471 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "\n");
2472 }
2473#endif
2474 lhspsdx = ASLHS(asx);
2475 switch (PSD_TYPE(lhspsdx)) {
2476 case TT_PSYM:
2477 case TT_ISYM:
2478 /* LHS is imprecise symbol; this is a MAY POINTS TO relationship */
2479 add_tptelist(lhspsdx, rhsptelistx);
2480 break;
2481
2482 case TT_GLOB:
2483 /* this is used when globals might be modified */
2484 add_tptelist(lhspsdx, rhsptelistx);
2485 /* must also modify target list for any global pointer source */
2486 for (sl = 1; sl < gpsd.nslots; ++sl) {
2487 if (is_source_global(SLOT(sl))) {
2488 add_tptelist(SLOT(sl), rhsptelistx);
2489 }
2490 }
2491 break;
2492
2493 case TT_IND:
2494 case TT_IIND:
2495 /* need to handle this */
2496 add_target_tptelist(lhspsdx, rhsptelistx);
2497 Trace(("indirect LHS type in assignment"));
2498 break;
2499 case TT_UNK:
2500 case TT_UNINIT: /* should not happen */
2501 unk_all();
2502 break;
2503 case TT_MEM:
2504 /* ### really want to handle member LHS types */
2505 interr("pointsto: unknown LHS type in assignment", PSD_TYPE(lhspsdx), ERR_Warning);
2506 Trace(("unknown LHS type in assignment"));
2507 break;
2508 default:
2509 /* real error */
2510 interr("pointsto: unknown LHS type in assignment", PSD_TYPE(lhspsdx), ERR_Fatal);
2511 Trace(("unknown LHS type in assignment"));
2512 break;
2513 }
2514#if DEBUG
2515 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
2516 puttarget(PSD_SLOT(lhspsdx));
2517 }
2518#endif
2519 free_list(rhsptelistx);
2520 break;
2521 case AS_UNK:
2522 lhspsdx = ASLHS(asx);
2523 switch (PSD_TYPE(lhspsdx)) {
2524 case TT_GLOB:
2525 /* shouldn't happen. Mark all globals as unknown */
2526 unk_globals();
2527 break;
2528 case TT_UNK:
2529 case TT_UNINIT: /* should not happen */
2530 unk_all();
2531 break;
2532 default:
2533 replace_tptelist(lhspsdx, TPTE_UNK);
2534 break;
2535 }
2536 break;
2537 case AS_CLEAR:
2538 break;
2539 default:
2540 break;
2541 }
2542#if DEBUG
2543 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
2544 Trace(("after assignment"));
2545 puttargets();
2546 }
2547#endif
2548} /* interpret */

2550/*
2551 * compare lptex and ptex; if they have the same or comparable type,
2552 * compare subtypes. If they all compare exactly, return ptex.
2553 * if they compare imprecisely, change ptex to be as imprecise as lptex,
2554 * and return -ptex if changes were made.
2555 */
2556static int
2557imprecise_match(int lptex, int ptex)
2558{
2559 int m;
2560 if (TPTE_STRIDE(lptex) != TPTE_STRIDE(ptex))
2561 return 0;
2562 if (TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(lptex)) == TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(ptex))) {
2563 switch (TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(lptex))) {
2564 case TT_PSYM:
2565 case TT_ISYM:
2566 if (TPTE_SPTR(lptex) == TPTE_SPTR(ptex))
2567 return ptex;
2568 return 0;
2569
2570 case TT_IND:
2571 case TT_IIND:
2572 return imprecise_match(TPTE_VAL(lptex), TPTE_VAL(ptex));
2573
2574 case TT_GDYN:
2575 case TT_IGDYN:
2576 case TT_LDYN:
2577 case TT_ILDYN:
2578 case TT_ANON:
2579 if (TPTE_VAL(lptex) == TPTE_VAL(ptex))
2580 return ptex;
2581 return 0;
2582
2583 case TT_CON:
2584 if (TPTE_VAL(lptex) == TPTE_VAL(ptex))
2585 return ptex;
2586 return 0;
2587 case TT_UNINIT:
2588 case TT_UNK:
2589 case TT_NLOC:
2590 return ptex;
2591 default:
2592 /* real error */
2593 interr("pointsto: unknown TPTE target type", TPTE_TYPE(lptex), ERR_Fatal);
2594 return 0;
2595 }
2596 } else {
2597 /* not quite an exact match */
2598 switch (TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(lptex))) {
2599 case TT_PSYM:
2600 /* might match TT_ISYM, if the same symbol */
2601 if (TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(ptex)) == TT_ISYM &&
2602 TPTE_SPTR(lptex) == TPTE_SPTR(ptex))
2603 return ptex;
2604 return 0;
2605 case TT_ISYM:
2606 /* might match TT_PSYM, if the same symbol, but change to ISYM */
2607 if (TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(ptex)) == TT_PSYM &&
2608 TPTE_SPTR(lptex) == TPTE_SPTR(ptex)) {
2609 TPTE_APTEX(ptex) = get_apte(TT_ISYM, TPTE_SPTR(ptex), TPTE_VAL(ptex),
2610 TPTE_STRIDE(ptex)
2611 );
2612 return -ptex;
2613 }
2614 return 0;
2615 case TT_IND:
2616 /* might match TT_IIND, if the subtypes match */
2617 if (TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(ptex)) == TT_IIND) {
2618 m = imprecise_match(TPTE_VAL(lptex), TPTE_VAL(ptex));
2619 if (m > 0)
2620 return ptex;
2621 if (m < 0)
2622 return -ptex;
2623 }
2624 return 0;
2625 case TT_IIND:
2626 /* might match TT_IND, if the subtypes match, but change to IIND */
2627 if (TTMASK(TPTE_TYPE(ptex)) == TT_IND) {
2628 m = imprecise_match(TPTE_VAL(lptex), TPTE_VAL(ptex));
2629 if (m != 0) {
2630 TPTE_APTEX(ptex) = get_apte(TT_IIND, TPTE_SPTR(ptex), TPTE_VAL(ptex),
2631 TPTE_STRIDE(ptex)
2632 );
2633 return -ptex;
2634 }
2635 }
2636 return 0;
2637 default:
2638 /* no other imprecise matches */
2639 return 0;
2640 }
2641 }
2642} /* imprecise_match */
2643
2644/*
2645 * look along the list at ptelistx; find a match for lptex;
2646 * an imprecise match is good enough. If lptex is less precise
2647 * than the one found, change the one found to be just as imprecise.
2648 * return 0 if not found, >0 if exact match found, <0 if changes were made
2649 */
2650static int
2651find_imprecise_match(int lptex, int ptelistx)
2652{
2653 int ptex, m;
2654 for (ptex = ptelistx; ptex > 0; ptex = TPTE_NEXT(ptex)) {
2655 m = imprecise_match(lptex, ptex);
2656 if (m != 0)
2657 return m;
2658 }
2659 return 0;
2660} /* find_imprecise_match */
2661
2662/*
2663 * combine (take the 'meet') of the information at the head of
2664 * node v with the new local information we have. return TRUE if it
2665 * changes at all
2666 */
2667static int
2668pte_changed(int v)
2669{
2670 int changes = 0;
2671 int sl;
2672 int lptex, hptex, newptex, newptelistx;
2673 Trace(("Combine information into node %d block %d", v, FG_TO_BIH(v)));
2674#if DEBUG
2675 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT))
2676 putnodetargets("before", v);
2677#endif
2678 for (sl = 1; sl < gpsd.nslots; ++sl) {
2679 if (HEAD(v, sl) == TPTE_UNK) {
2680 /* already worst case, give up */
2681 } else if (LHEAD(sl) == TPTE_UNK) {
2682 free_list(HEAD(v, sl));
2683 HEAD(v, sl) = TPTE_UNK;
2684 ++changes;
2685 } else if (HEAD(v, sl) == TTE_NULL || HEAD(v, sl) == TPTE_UNINIT) {
2686 if (LHEAD(sl) != TTE_NULL) {
2687 HEAD(v, sl) = copy_list(LHEAD(sl));
2688 ++changes;
2689 }
2690 } else if (LHEAD(sl) == TTE_NULL) {
2691 /* nothing to add */
2692 } else {
2693 /* compare pointer targets one at a time */
2694 /* collect all new PTEs here */
2695 newptelistx = TTE_NULL;
2696 for (lptex = LHEAD(sl); lptex > 0; lptex = TPTE_NEXT(lptex)) {
2697 /* find a matching or almost-matching TPTE in HEAD */
2698 hptex = find_imprecise_match(lptex, HEAD(v, sl));
2699 if (hptex == 0) {
2700 newptex = copy_pte(lptex, 0, 1);
2701 TPTE_NEXT(newptex) = newptelistx;
2702 newptelistx = newptex;
2703 ++changes;
2704 } else if (hptex < 0) {
2705 /* flag that something changed */
2706 ++changes;
2707 }
2708 }
2709 /* add newptelistx to HEAD(v,sl) */
2710 if (newptelistx > 0) {
2711 for (newptex = newptelistx; TPTE_NEXT(newptex) > 0;
2712 newptex = TPTE_NEXT(newptex))
2713 ;
2714 TPTE_NEXT(newptex) = HEAD(v, sl);
2715 HEAD(v, sl) = newptelistx;
2716 }
2717 }
2718 }
2719#if DEBUG
2720 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT) && changes)
2721 putnodetargets(" after", v);
2722#endif
2723 return changes;
2724} /* pte_changed */
2725
2726#if DEBUG
2727static int
2728check_this_assignment(int asx, int v)
2729{
2730 int ptex;
2731 if (ASTYPE(asx) == AS_DIRECT || ASTYPE(asx) == AS_INIT ||
2732 ASTYPE(asx) == AS_ADD_DIRECT) {
2733 ptex = ASRHS(asx);
2734 if (ptex >= gpte.stg_avail) {
2735 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "TPTE(%d) is on list for node %d, assignment %d, but "
2736 "past avail point %d\n",
2737 ptex, v, asx, gpte.stg_avail);
2738 return 1;
2739 } else if (TPTE_FLAG(ptex) == 0) {
2740 TPTE_FLAG(ptex) = -asx;
2741 } else if (TPTE_FLAG(ptex) == -9999999) {
2742 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "TPTE(%d) is on list for node %d, assignment %d, but "
2743 "also on free list\n",
2744 ptex, v, asx);
2745 return 1;
2746 } else if (TPTE_FLAG(ptex) < 0) {
2747 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "TPTE(%d) is on list for node %d, assignment %d, but "
2748 "also on list for assignment %d\n",
2749 ptex, v, asx, -TPTE_FLAG(ptex));
2750 return 1;
2751 } else if (TPTE_FLAG(ptex) > 0) {
2752 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "TPTE(%d) is on list for node %d, assignment %d, but "
2753 "also on list for node %d\n",
2754 ptex, v, asx, TPTE_FLAG(ptex));
2755 return 1;
2756 }
2757 }
2758 return 0;
2759} /* check_this_assignment */

2761/*
2762 * see that all TPTE entries are on a list somewhere
2763 */
2764static void
2765check_pte(const char *ch)
2766{
2767 int v, sl, ptex, bad, asx, stdx;
2768 for (ptex = 1; ptex < gpte.stg_avail; ++ptex)
2769 TPTE_FLAG(ptex) = 0;
2770 /* mark the free list */
2771 bad = 0;
2772 for (ptex = gpte.xstg_free; ptex > 0; ptex = TPTE_NEXT(ptex)) {
2773 if (ptex >= gpte.stg_avail) {
2774 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "TPTE(%d) is on free list but past avail point %d\n",
2775 ptex, gpte.stg_avail);
2776 bad = 1;
2777 break;
2778 } else if (TPTE_FLAG(ptex) == 0) {
2779 TPTE_FLAG(ptex) = -9999999;
2780 } else {
2781 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "TPTE(%d) is on free list twice\n", ptex);
2782 bad = 1;
2783 break;
2784 }
2785 }
2786 /* mark pte on target list of each slot at each node */
2787 for (v = 1; v <= opt.num_nodes; ++v) {
2788 if (nodeoffset[v] == 0)
2789 continue;
2790 for (sl = 1; sl < gpsd.nslots; ++sl) {
2791 if (HEAD(v, sl) != TPTE_UNINIT) {
2792 for (ptex = HEAD(v, sl); ptex > 0; ptex = TPTE_NEXT(ptex)) {
2793 if (ptex >= gpte.stg_avail) {
2794 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "TPTE(%d) is on list for node %d, slot %d, but "
2795 "past avail point %d\n",
2796 ptex, v, sl, gpte.stg_avail);
2797 bad = 1;
2798 break;
2799 } else if (TPTE_FLAG(ptex) == 0) {
2800 TPTE_FLAG(ptex) = v;
2801 } else if (TPTE_FLAG(ptex) == -9999999) {
2802 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "TPTE(%d) is on list for node %d, slot %d, but "
2803 "also on free list\n",
2804 ptex, v, sl);
2805 bad = 1;
2806 break;
2807 } else if (TPTE_FLAG(ptex) < 0) {
2808 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "TPTE(%d) is on list for node %d, slot %d, but "
2809 "also on list for assignment %d\n",
2810 ptex, v, sl, -TPTE_FLAG(ptex));
2811 bad = 1;
2812 break;
2813 } else if (TPTE_FLAG(ptex) > 0) {
2814 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "TPTE(%d) is on list for node %d, slot %d, but "
2815 "also on list for node %d\n",
2816 ptex, v, sl, TPTE_FLAG(ptex));
2817 bad = 1;
2818 break;
2819 }
2820 }
2821 }
2822 }
2823/* mark pte on direct assignments */
2824 for (stdx = FG_STDFIRST(v); stdx; stdx = STD_NEXT(stdx)) {
2825 for (asx = FIRSTAS(stdx); asx > 0; asx = ASNEXT(asx)) {
2826 bad += check_this_assignment(asx, stdx);
2827 }
2828 if (stdx == FG_STDLAST(v))
2829 break;
2830 }
2831 /* also check any unreachable statements following this node up to
2832 * the next node */
2833 stdx = FG_STDLAST(v);
2834 for (stdx = STD_NEXT(stdx); stdx && STD_FG(stdx) == 0;
2835 stdx = STD_NEXT(stdx)) {
2836 for (asx = FIRSTAS(stdx); asx > 0; asx = ASNEXT(asx)) {
2837 bad += check_this_assignment(asx, stdx);
2838 }
2839 }
2840 }
2841 for (ptex = 2; ptex < gpte.stg_avail; ++ptex) {
2842 if (TPTE_FLAG(ptex) == 0) {
2843 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "TPTE(%d) is not on any list\n", ptex);
2844 bad = 1;
2845 }
2846 }
2847 if (bad) {
2848 /* real error, consistency check failure */
2849 interr(ch, 0, ERR_Fatal);
2850 }
2851} /* check_pte */
2852#endif

3170static bool
3171different_pta(int pta1, int pta2)
3172{
3173 int p1, p2;
3174 for (; pta1 && pta2; pta1 = FPSRC_NEXT(pta1), pta2 = FPSRC_NEXT(pta2)) {
3175 if (FPSRC_TYPE(pta1) != FPSRC_TYPE(pta2))
3176 return TRUE;
3177 if (FPSRC_SPTR(pta1) != FPSRC_SPTR(pta2))
3178 return TRUE;
3179 for (p1 = FPSRC_PTELIST(pta1), p2 = FPSRC_PTELIST(pta2); p1 && p2;
3180 p1 = FPTE_NEXT(p1), p2 = FPTE_NEXT(p2)) {
3181 if (FPTE_TYPE(p1) != FPTE_TYPE(p2))
3182 return TRUE;
3183 if (FPTE_SPTR(p1) != FPTE_SPTR(p2))
3184 return TRUE;
3185 if (FPTE_VAL(p1) != FPTE_VAL(p2))
3186 return TRUE;
3187 if (FPTE_STRIDE(p1) != FPTE_STRIDE(p2))
3188 return TRUE;
3189 }
3190 if (p1 || p1)
3191 return TRUE;
3192 }
3193 if (pta1 || pta2)
3194 return TRUE;
3195 /* identical lists */
3196 return FALSE;
3197} /* different_pta */
