3199/*
3200 * Make a copy of the current list for the current statement
3201 * we can use the same list as for the last std if 'change' == 0
3202 */
3203
3204static void
3205set_std_pta(int stdx, int change)
3206{
3207 int sl, psdx, ptex, this_pta, nthis_pta, save_fpte_avail, save_fpsrc_avail;
3208 if (last_pta && !change) {
3209 STD_PTA(stdx) = last_pta;
3210 } else {
3211 this_pta = 0;
3212 save_fpte_avail = fpte.stg_avail;
3213 save_fpsrc_avail = fpsrc.stg_avail;
3214 for (sl = 1; sl < gpsd.nslots; ++sl) {
3215 if (LHEAD(sl) != TTE_NULL && LHEAD(sl) != TPTE_UNK) {
3216 psdx = SLOT(sl);
3217 nthis_pta = add_fpsrc(psdx, this_pta);
3218 if (nthis_pta != this_pta) {
3219 this_pta = nthis_pta;
3220 for (ptex = LHEAD(sl); ptex > 0; ptex = TPTE_NEXT(ptex)) {
3221 add_fpte(ptex, this_pta);
3222 }
3223 }
3224 }
3225 }
3226 if (!different_pta(this_pta, last_pta)) {
3227 fpte.stg_avail = save_fpte_avail;
3228 fpsrc.stg_avail = save_fpsrc_avail;
3229 this_pta = last_pta;
3230 }
3231 STD_PTA(stdx) = this_pta;
3232 last_pta = this_pta;
3233 }
3234} /* set_std_pta */
3235
3236/*
3237 * used externally
3238 * using the previously collected pointer target information,
3239 * try to determine whether the pointer at ptrsptr might point to
3240 * the symbol targetsptr, or, if targetsptr is itself a pointer,
3241 * might point to the same target as targetsptr
3242 * return TRUE if we know nothing, or we know (or believe) they might conflict
3243 * return FALSE if we can prove they don't conflict
3244 *
3245 * arguments are the std indices for the pointer and target references,
3246 * the base SPTRs of the references,
3247 * whether the target reference has the TARGET attribute
3248 * and whether the target also has the pointer attribute
3249 *
3250 * possible targets are:
3251 * psym - precise symbol, with symbol sptr
3252 * isym - imprecise symbol, perhaps a member of derived type, with base sptr
3253 * anon - some anonymous symbol, we have no more information, but an
3254 *identifying tag
3255 * this information comes from IPA
3256 * nloc - nonlocal targets - anything but a local symbol, used for initial
3257 *values
3258 * ldyn - locally allocated dynamic memory, with unique tag for each allocate
3259 *point
3260 * gdyn - dynamically allocated memory from somewhere outside this routine
3261 * from IPA
3262 * con - used for NULLIFY statements, DEALLOCATE statements, essentially null
3263 *pointer
3264 * unk - unknown
3265 *
3266 * possible conflicts for pointer and target are:
3267 * ptr
3268 * psym conflict if psym sptr matches target
3269 * isym conflict if psym sptr matches target
3270 * anon no conflict - IPA only uses anon when this routine does not
3271 *see the symbol
3272 * nloc conflict if target is not a local (common, or host)
3273 * ldyn no conflict
3274 * gdyn no conflict
3275 * con no conflict (null doesn't conflict with anything)
3276 * unk conflict
3277 * default conflict
3278 *
3279 * possible conflicts for two pointers are:
3280 *
3281 * psym isym anon nloc ldyn gdyn con
3282 *unk default
3283 * psym MAY(1) MAY(1) no MAY(2) no no
3284 *never YES YES
3285 * isym MAY(1) MAY(1) no MAY(2) no no
3286 *never YES YES
3287 * anon no no MAY(3) YES(4) no no never
3288 *YES YES
3289 * nloc MAY(2) MAY(2) YES(4) YES no YES(4)
3290 *never YES YES
3291 * ldyn no no no no MAY(3) no never
3292 *YES YES
3293 * gdyn no no no YES(4) no MAY(3) never
3294 *YES YES
3295 * con never never never never never never
3296 *never never never
3297 * unk YES YES YES YES YES YES never
3298 *YES YES
3299 * default YES YES YES YES YES YES never
3300 *YES YES
3301 *
3302 * this matrix should be symmetric
3303 * notes:
3304 * (1) two symbol targets conflict if the sptrs are the same
3305 * (2) symbol and nloc conflict if the symbol is not local
3306 * (3) two anons, ldyns, gdyns conflict if the unique value is the same
3307 * (4) nloc conflicts with anon and gdyn because nloc is a nonlocal target, anon
3308 *is
3309 * an anonymous global memory location
3310 */
3311
3312#undef TRACEFLAG
3313#undef TRACEBIT
3314#define TRACEFLAG 10
3315#define TRACEBIT 0x1000000
3316
3317bool
3318pta_conflict(int ptrstdx, int ptrsptr, int targetstdx, int targetsptr,
3319 int targetpointer, int targettarget)
3320{
3321 int ptrsrc, targetsrc, ptrpte, targetpte;
3322 if (fpsrc.stg_base == NULL)
3323 return TRUE;
3324 /* see whether we have information about pointer targets for source ptrsptr at
3325 * statement ptrstdx */
3326 ptrsrc = STD_PTA(ptrstdx);
3327 for (; ptrsrc; ptrsrc = FPSRC_NEXT(ptrsrc)) {
3328 if (FPSRC_SPTR(ptrsrc) == ptrsptr)
3329 break;
3330 }
3331 if (ptrsrc == 0) {
3332#if DEBUG
3333 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
3334 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pointer %d:%s in std:%d may point to POINTER symbol "
3335 "%d:%s in std:%d\n pointer pointees are unknown\n",
3336 ptrsptr, SYMNAME(ptrsptr), ptrstdx, targetsptr,
3337 SYMNAME(targetsptr), targetstdx);
3338 }
3339#endif
3340 return TRUE; /* we know nothing about what this pointer targets */
3341 }
3342
3343 if (targettarget) {
3344 /* 'target' has TARGET attribute. see if ptr can point to target */
3345 for (ptrpte = FPSRC_PTELIST(ptrsrc); ptrpte; ptrpte = FPTE_NEXT(ptrpte)) {
3346 switch (FPTE_TYPE(ptrpte)) {
3347 case TT_PSYM:
3348 case TT_ISYM:
3349 /* does the symbol match? */
3350 if (FPTE_SPTR(ptrpte) == targetsptr) {
3351#if DEBUG
3352 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
3353 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pointer %d:%s in std:%d may point to TARGET "
3354 "symbol %d:%s in std:%d\n pointer targets the "
3355 "symbol directly\n",
3356 ptrsptr, SYMNAME(ptrsptr), ptrstdx, targetsptr,
3357 SYMNAME(targetsptr), targetstdx);
3358 }
3359#endif
3360 return TRUE;
3361 }
3362 break;
3363 case TT_ANON:
3364 case TT_GDYN:
3365 case TT_IGDYN:
3366 case TT_LDYN:
3367 case TT_ILDYN:
3368 case TT_CON:
3369 /* these don't conflict with any symbol */
3370 break;
3371 case TT_NLOC:
3372 /* is targetsptr a nonlocal? */
3373 if (gbl.internal > 1 && !INTERNALG(targetsptr)) {
3374#if DEBUG
3375 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
3376 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pointer %d:%s in std:%d may point to TARGET "
3377 "symbol %d:%s in std:%d\n pointer targets "
3378 "nonlocal memory, target is from the host\n",
3379 ptrsptr, SYMNAME(ptrsptr), ptrstdx, targetsptr,
3380 SYMNAME(targetsptr), targetstdx);
3381 }
3382#endif
3383 return TRUE;
3384 } else {
3385 switch (SCG(targetsptr)) {
3386 case SC_CMBLK:
3387 case SC_EXTERN:
3388#if DEBUG
3389 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
3390 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pointer %d:%s in std:%d may point to TARGET "
3391 "symbol %d:%s in std:%d\n pointer targets "
3392 "nonlocal memory, target is global\n",
3393 ptrsptr, SYMNAME(ptrsptr), ptrstdx, targetsptr,
3394 SYMNAME(targetsptr), targetstdx);
3395 }
3396#endif
3397 return TRUE;
3398 default:;
3399 }
3400 }
3401 break;
3402 case TT_UNK:
3403 case TT_UNINIT:
3404/* might point anywhere */
3405#if DEBUG
3406 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
3407 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pointer %d:%s in std:%d may point to TARGET "
3408 "symbol %d:%s in std:%d pointer may point "
3409 "anywhere\n",
3410 ptrsptr, SYMNAME(ptrsptr), ptrstdx, targetsptr,
3411 SYMNAME(targetsptr), targetstdx);
3412 }
3413#endif
3414 return TRUE;
3415 case TT_IND:
3416 case TT_IIND:
3417 case TT_MEM:
3418 case TT_GLOB:
3419 default:
3420/* should not appear */
3421#if DEBUG
3422 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
3423 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pointer %d:%s in std:%d may point to TARGET "
3424 "symbol %d:%s in std:%d unexpected condition\n",
3425 ptrsptr, SYMNAME(ptrsptr), ptrstdx, targetsptr,
3426 SYMNAME(targetsptr), targetstdx);
3427 }
3428#endif
3429 return TRUE;
3430 }
3431 }
3432 }
3433
3434 if (targetpointer) {
3435 /* target has the pointer attribute as well */
3436 targetsrc = STD_PTA(targetstdx);
3437 for (; targetsrc; targetsrc = FPSRC_NEXT(targetsrc)) {
3438 if (FPSRC_SPTR(targetsrc) == targetsptr)
3439 break;
3440 }
3441 if (targetsrc == 0) {
3442#if DEBUG
3443 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
3444 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pointer %d:%s in std:%d may point to POINTER "
3445 "symbol %d:%s in std:%d\n target pointees are "
3446 "unknown\n",
3447 ptrsptr, SYMNAME(ptrsptr), ptrstdx, targetsptr,
3448 SYMNAME(targetsptr), targetstdx);
3449 }
3450#endif
3451 return TRUE; /* we know nothing about what this pointer targets */
3452 }
3453
3454 /* compare the two pointer target lists for a match */
3455 for (ptrpte = FPSRC_PTELIST(ptrsrc); ptrpte; ptrpte = FPTE_NEXT(ptrpte)) {
3456 switch (FPTE_TYPE(ptrpte)) {
3457 case TT_UNK:
3458 case TT_UNINIT:
3459/* ptr might point anywhere */
3460#if DEBUG
3461 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
3462 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pointer %d:%s in std:%d may point to POINTER "
3463 "symbol %d:%s in std:%d\n pointer may point "
3464 "anywhere\n",
3465 ptrsptr, SYMNAME(ptrsptr), ptrstdx, targetsptr,
3466 SYMNAME(targetsptr), targetstdx);
3467 }
3468#endif
3469 return TRUE;
3470 case TT_IND:
3471 case TT_IIND:
3472 case TT_MEM:
3473 case TT_GLOB:
3474 default:
3475/* should not appear */
3476#if DEBUG
3477 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
3478 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pointer %d:%s in std:%d may point to POINTER "
3479 "symbol %d:%s in std:%d\n unexpected condition\n",
3480 ptrsptr, SYMNAME(ptrsptr), ptrstdx, targetsptr,
3481 SYMNAME(targetsptr), targetstdx);
3482 }
3483#endif
3484 return TRUE;
3485 case TT_CON:
3486 if (FPTE_VAL(ptrpte) != 0) {
3487#if DEBUG
3488 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
3489 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pointer %d:%s in std:%d may point to POINTER "
3490 "symbol %d:%s in std:%d\n pointer may point to "
3491 "nonnull constant\n",
3492 ptrsptr, SYMNAME(ptrsptr), ptrstdx, targetsptr,
3493 SYMNAME(targetsptr), targetstdx);
3494 }
3495#endif
3496 return TRUE;
3497 }
3498 break;
3499 case TT_PSYM:
3500 case TT_ISYM:
3501 case TT_ANON:
3502 case TT_GDYN:
3503 case TT_IGDYN:
3504 case TT_LDYN:
3505 case TT_ILDYN:
3506 case TT_NLOC:
3507 break;
3508 }
3509 for (targetpte = FPSRC_PTELIST(targetsrc); targetpte;
3510 targetpte = FPTE_NEXT(targetpte)) {
3511 switch (FPTE_TYPE(targetpte)) {
3512 case TT_UNK:
3513 case TT_UNINIT:
3514/* target might point anywhere */
3515#if DEBUG
3516 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
3517 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pointer %d:%s in std:%d may point to POINTER "
3518 "symbol %d:%s in std:%d\n target may point "
3519 "anywhere\n",
3520 ptrsptr, SYMNAME(ptrsptr), ptrstdx, targetsptr,
3521 SYMNAME(targetsptr), targetstdx);
3522 }
3523#endif
3524 return TRUE;
3525 case TT_IND:
3526 case TT_IIND:
3527 case TT_MEM:
3528 case TT_GLOB:
3529 default:
3530/* should not appear */
3531#if DEBUG
3532 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
3533 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pointer %d:%s in std:%d may point to POINTER "
3534 "symbol %d:%s in std:%d\n unexpected target "
3535 "condition\n",
3536 ptrsptr, SYMNAME(ptrsptr), ptrstdx, targetsptr,
3537 SYMNAME(targetsptr), targetstdx);
3538 }
3539#endif
3540 return TRUE;
3541 case TT_CON:
3542 if (FPTE_VAL(targetpte) != 0) {
3543#if DEBUG
3544 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
3545 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pointer %d:%s in std:%d may point to "
3546 "POINTER symbol %d:%s in std:%d\n target may "
3547 "point to nonnull constant\n",
3548 ptrsptr, SYMNAME(ptrsptr), ptrstdx, targetsptr,
3549 SYMNAME(targetsptr), targetstdx);
3550 }
3551#endif
3552 return TRUE;
3553 }
3554 break;
3555 case TT_PSYM:
3556 case TT_ISYM:
3557 case TT_ANON:
3558 case TT_GDYN:
3559 case TT_IGDYN:
3560 case TT_LDYN:
3561 case TT_ILDYN:
3562 case TT_NLOC:
3563 break;
3564 }
3565
3566 switch (FPTE_TYPE(ptrpte)) {
3567 case TT_PSYM:
3568 case TT_ISYM:
3569 switch (FPTE_TYPE(targetpte)) {
3570 case TT_PSYM:
3571 case TT_ISYM:
3572 /* do the symbols match? */
3573 if (FPTE_SPTR(ptrpte) == FPTE_SPTR(targetpte)) {
3574#if DEBUG
3575 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
3576 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pointer %d:%s in std:%d may point to "
3577 "POINTER symbol %d:%s in std:%d\n both may "
3578 "point to %d:%s\n",
3579 ptrsptr, SYMNAME(ptrsptr), ptrstdx, targetsptr,
3580 SYMNAME(targetsptr), targetstdx, FPTE_SPTR(ptrpte),
3581 SYMNAME(FPTE_SPTR(ptrpte)));
3582 }
3583#endif
3584 return TRUE;
3585 }
3586 break;
3587 case TT_NLOC:
3588 /* is ptr symbol a nonlocal? */
3589 if (gbl.internal > 1 && !INTERNALG(FPTE_SPTR(ptrpte))) {
3590#if DEBUG
3591 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
3592 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pointer %d:%s in std:%d may point to "
3593 "POINTER symbol %d:%s in std:%d\n pointer "
3594 "may point to %d:%s, target may point to "
3595 "nonlocal\n",
3596 ptrsptr, SYMNAME(ptrsptr), ptrstdx, targetsptr,
3597 SYMNAME(targetsptr), targetstdx, FPTE_SPTR(ptrpte),
3598 SYMNAME(FPTE_SPTR(ptrpte)));
3599 }
3600#endif
3601 return TRUE;
3602 } else {
3603 switch (SCG(FPTE_SPTR(ptrpte))) {
3604 case SC_CMBLK:
3605 case SC_EXTERN:
3606#if DEBUG
3607 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
3608 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pointer %d:%s in std:%d may point to "
3609 "POINTER symbol %d:%s in std:%d\n "
3610 "pointer may point to %d:%s, target may "
3611 "point to common\n",
3612 ptrsptr, SYMNAME(ptrsptr), ptrstdx, targetsptr,
3613 SYMNAME(targetsptr), targetstdx, FPTE_SPTR(ptrpte),
3614 SYMNAME(FPTE_SPTR(ptrpte)));
3615 }
3616#endif
3617 return TRUE;
3618 default:;
3619 }
3620 }
3621 break;
3622 /* symbols do not conflict with ldyn, gdyn, anon;
3623 * unk and default cases already handled */
3624 }
3625 break;
3626 case TT_LDYN:
3627 case TT_ILDYN:
3628 /* only conflicts with the another local dynamic and value */
3629 if (FPTE_TYPE(targetpte) == FPTE_TYPE(ptrpte)) {
3630 if (FPTE_VAL(targetpte) == FPTE_VAL(ptrpte)) {
3631#if DEBUG
3632 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
3633 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pointer %d:%s in std:%d may point to "
3634 "POINTER symbol %d:%s in std:%d\n both "
3635 "point to local dynamically allocated "
3636 "memory\n",
3637 ptrsptr, SYMNAME(ptrsptr), ptrstdx, targetsptr,
3638 SYMNAME(targetsptr), targetstdx);
3639 }
3640#endif
3641 return TRUE;
3642 }
3643 }
3644 /* else no conflict from this target */
3645 break;
3646 case TT_ANON:
3647 case TT_GDYN:
3648 case TT_IGDYN:
3649 /* conflicts with same type and value,
3650 * also conflicts with NLOC */
3651 if (FPTE_TYPE(targetpte) == FPTE_TYPE(ptrpte)) {
3652 if (FPTE_VAL(targetpte) == FPTE_VAL(ptrpte)) {
3653#if DEBUG
3654 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
3655 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pointer %d:%s in std:%d may point to "
3656 "POINTER symbol %d:%s in std:%d\n both may "
3657 "point to globally allocated memory\n",
3658 ptrsptr, SYMNAME(ptrsptr), ptrstdx, targetsptr,
3659 SYMNAME(targetsptr), targetstdx);
3660 }
3661#endif
3662 return TRUE;
3663 }
3664 } else if (FPTE_TYPE(targetpte) == TT_NLOC) {
3665#if DEBUG
3666 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
3667 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pointer %d:%s in std:%d may point to "
3668 "POINTER symbol %d:%s in std:%d\n pointer "
3669 "may point to globally allocated memory, "
3670 "target may point to nonlocal\n",
3671 ptrsptr, SYMNAME(ptrsptr), ptrstdx, targetsptr,
3672 SYMNAME(targetsptr), targetstdx);
3673 }
3674#endif
3675 return TRUE;
3676 }
3677 break;
3678 case TT_CON:
3679 /* NULL pointer doesn't conflict */
3680 break;
3681 case TT_NLOC:
3682 /* conflicts with nonlocal, anon, gdyn, any nonlocal symbol */
3683 switch (FPTE_TYPE(targetpte)) {
3684 case TT_NLOC:
3685 case TT_GDYN:
3686 case TT_IGDYN:
3687 case TT_ANON:
3688#if DEBUG
3689 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
3690 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pointer %d:%s in std:%d may point to "
3691 "POINTER symbol %d:%s in std:%d\n pointer "
3692 "may point to nonlocal, target may point to "
3693 "nonlocal or global dynamic or anonymous\n",
3694 ptrsptr, SYMNAME(ptrsptr), ptrstdx, targetsptr,
3695 SYMNAME(targetsptr), targetstdx);
3696 }
3697#endif
3698 return TRUE;
3699 case TT_PSYM:
3700 case TT_ISYM:
3701 /* is targetsptr a nonlocal? */
3702 if (gbl.internal > 1 && !INTERNALG(FPTE_SPTR(targetpte))) {
3703#if DEBUG
3704 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
3705 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pointer %d:%s in std:%d may point to "
3706 "POINTER symbol %d:%s in std:%d\n pointer "
3707 "may point to nonlocal, target may point "
3708 "to %d:%s which is from the host\n",
3709 ptrsptr, SYMNAME(ptrsptr), ptrstdx, targetsptr,
3710 SYMNAME(targetsptr), targetstdx, FPTE_SPTR(targetpte),
3711 SYMNAME(FPTE_SPTR(targetpte)));
3712 }
3713#endif
3714 return TRUE;
3715 } else {
3716 switch (SCG(FPTE_SPTR(targetpte))) {
3717 case SC_CMBLK:
3718 case SC_EXTERN:
3719#if DEBUG
3720 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
3721 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pointer %d:%s in std:%d may point to "
3722 "POINTER symbol %d:%s in std:%d\n "
3723 "pointer may point to nonlocal, target "
3724 "may point to %d:%s which is external\n",
3725 ptrsptr, SYMNAME(ptrsptr), ptrstdx, targetsptr,
3726 SYMNAME(targetsptr), targetstdx, FPTE_SPTR(targetpte),
3727 SYMNAME(FPTE_SPTR(targetpte)));
3728 }
3729#endif
3730 return TRUE;
3731 default:;
3732 }
3733 }
3734 break;
3735 }
3736 break;
3737 }
3738 }
3739 }
3740 }
3741 return FALSE;
3742} /* pta_conflict */

3744/*
3745 * used externally
3746 * using the previously collected pointer target information,
3747 * try to determine whether the pointer at ptrsptr always points to aligned
3748 * data.
3749 * return TRUE if we know the pointer target is always quad aligned
3750 * return FALSE if we don't know or know otherwise
3751 *
3752 * arguments are the std indices for the pointer reference,
3753 * and the base SPTRs of the reference
3754 *
3755 * possible targets are:
3756 * psym - precise symbol, with symbol sptr
3757 * the target is aligned if the symbol is aligned and stride is one
3758 * isym - imprecise symbol, perhaps a member of derived type, with base sptr
3759 * unaligned
3760 * anon - some anonymous symbol, we have no more information, but an
3761 * identifying tag
3762 * this information comes from IPA
3763 * unaligned, unless we enhance this information from IPA
3764 * nloc - nonlocal targets - anything but a local symbol, used for initial
3765 * values
3766 * unaligned
3767 * ldyn - locally allocated dynamic memory, with unique tag for each allocate
3768 * point
3769 * aligned or unaligned, depending on whether it is precise and stride
3770 * is one
3771 * gdyn - dynamically allocated memory from somewhere outside this routine
3772 * from IPA
3773 * usually unaligned, unless we know it's precise and stride is one
3774 * con - used for NULLIFY statements, DEALLOCATE statements, essentially null
3775 * pointer
3776 * shouldn't happen, treat as aligned
3777 * unk - unknown
3778 * unaligned
3779 */
3780bool
3781pta_aligned(int ptrstdx, int ptrsptr)
3782{
3783 int ptrsrc, ptrpte, sptr;
3784 if (fpsrc.stg_base == NULL)
3785 return FALSE;
3786 /* see whether we have information about pointer targets for source ptrsptr at
3787 * statement ptrstdx */
3788 ptrsrc = STD_PTA(ptrstdx);
3789 for (; ptrsrc; ptrsrc = FPSRC_NEXT(ptrsrc)) {
3790 if (FPSRC_SPTR(ptrsrc) == ptrsptr)
3791 break;
3792 }
3793 if (ptrsrc == 0)
3794 return FALSE; /* we know nothing about what this pointer targets */
3795
3796 for (ptrpte = FPSRC_PTELIST(ptrsrc); ptrpte; ptrpte = FPTE_NEXT(ptrpte)) {
3797 switch (FPTE_TYPE(ptrpte)) {
3798 case TT_PSYM:
3799 /* might be aligned if the symbol is */
3800 sptr = FPTE_SPTR(ptrpte);
3801 if (!QALNG(sptr))
3802 return FALSE;
3803 if (FPTE_STRIDE(ptrpte) != 1)
3804 return FALSE;
3805 break;
3806 case TT_GDYN:
3807 if (FPTE_STRIDE(ptrpte) != 1)
3808 return FALSE;
3809 break;
3810 case TT_LDYN:
3811 if (FPTE_STRIDE(ptrpte) != 1)
3812 return FALSE;
3813 break;
3814 case TT_CON:
3815 break;
3816 case TT_ISYM: /* somewhere in the symbol */
3817 case TT_ANON: /* don't know where */
3818 case TT_ILDYN: /* somewhere in the allocated space */
3819 case TT_IGDYN:
3820 return FALSE;
3821 case TT_NLOC: /* some nonlocal symbol */
3822 case TT_UNK: /* anywhere */
3823 case TT_UNINIT: /* anywhere */
3824 /* might point anywhere */
3825 return FALSE;
3826 case TT_IND: /* some indirect location, shouldn't happen here */
3827 case TT_IIND:
3828 case TT_MEM:
3829 case TT_GLOB:
3830 default:
3831 /* should not appear */
3832 return FALSE;
3833 }
3834 }
3835 /* no show stoppers found == no misaligned targets found */
3836 return TRUE;
3837} /* pta_aligned */
3838
3839/*
3840 * used externally
3841 * using previous collected pointer target information,
3842 * determine whether the pointer target is always stride-1, meaning
3843 * for instance that it can be passed directly to an assumed-shape argument
3844 * without copying to a temp
3845 */
3846bool
3847pta_stride1(int ptrstdx, int ptrsptr)
3848{
3849 int ptrsrc, ptrpte;
3850 if (fpsrc.stg_base == NULL)
3851 return FALSE;
3852 /* see whether we have information about pointer targets for source ptrsptr at
3853 * statement ptrstdx */
3854 ptrsrc = STD_PTA(ptrstdx);
3855 for (; ptrsrc; ptrsrc = FPSRC_NEXT(ptrsrc)) {
3856 if (FPSRC_SPTR(ptrsrc) == ptrsptr)
3857 break;
3858 }
3859 if (ptrsrc == 0)
3860 return FALSE; /* we know nothing about what this pointer targets */
3861
3862 for (ptrpte = FPSRC_PTELIST(ptrsrc); ptrpte; ptrpte = FPTE_NEXT(ptrpte)) {
3863 switch (FPTE_TYPE(ptrpte)) {
3864 case TT_PSYM:
3865 case TT_ISYM: /* somewhere in the symbol */
3866 if (FPTE_STRIDE(ptrpte) != 1)
3867 return FALSE;
3868 break;
3869 case TT_GDYN:
3870 case TT_IGDYN:
3871 if (FPTE_STRIDE(ptrpte) != 1)
3872 return FALSE;
3873 break;
3874 case TT_LDYN:
3875 case TT_ILDYN: /* somewhere in the allocated space */
3876 if (FPTE_STRIDE(ptrpte) != 1)
3877 return FALSE;
3878 break;
3879 case TT_CON:
3880 break;
3881 case TT_ANON: /* don't know where */
3882 case TT_NLOC: /* some nonlocal symbol */
3883 case TT_UNK: /* anywhere */
3884 case TT_UNINIT: /* anywhere */
3885 /* might point anywhere */
3886 return FALSE;
3887 case TT_IND: /* some indirect location, shouldn't happen here */
3888 case TT_IIND:
3889 case TT_MEM:
3890 case TT_GLOB:
3891 default:
3892 /* should not appear */
3893 return FALSE;
3894 }
3895 }
3896 /* no show stoppers found == only stride-1 targets found */
3897 return TRUE;
3898} /* pta_stride1 */

3900/*
3901 * used externally
3902 * using previous collected pointer target information,
3903 * determine whether there is pointer target information for this
3904 * statement/sptr
3905 * return a tag and id to describe it.
3906 * tag may be one of:
3907 * 0 = no more information
3908 * 1 = unknown target
3909 * 2 = local dynamically allocated memory (tag disambiguates)
3910 * 3 = global dynamically allocated memory (tag disambiguates)
3911 * 4 = nonlocal memory (tag disambiguates)
3912 * 5 = precise symbol target (tag is sptr)
3913 * 6 = imprecise symbol target (tag is sptr)
3914 */
3915int
3916pta_target(int ptrstdx, int ptrsptr, int *ptag, int *pid)
3917{
3918 static int prev_func_count = 0, prevptrstdx = 0, prevptrsptr = 0, ptrsrc = 0,
3919 ptrpte = 0;
3920 if (fpsrc.stg_base == NULL)
3921 return 0;
3922 if (prevptrstdx == ptrstdx && prevptrsptr == ptrsptr &&
3923 prev_func_count == gbl.func_count) {
3924 ptrpte = FPTE_NEXT(ptrpte);
3925 } else {
3926 prev_func_count = gbl.func_count;
3927 ptrpte = 0;
3928 prevptrstdx = 0;
3929 prevptrsptr = 0;
3930 /* see whether we have information about pointer targets for source ptrsptr
3931 * at
3932 * statement ptrstdx */
3933 ptrsrc = STD_PTA(ptrstdx);
3934 for (; ptrsrc; ptrsrc = FPSRC_NEXT(ptrsrc)) {
3935 if (FPSRC_SPTR(ptrsrc) == ptrsptr)
3936 break;
3937 }
3938 if (ptrsrc == 0) {
3939 return 0; /* we know nothing about what this pointer targets */
3940 }
3941 prevptrstdx = ptrstdx;
3942 prevptrsptr = ptrsptr;
3943 ptrpte = FPSRC_PTELIST(ptrsrc);
3944 }
3945
3946 if (ptrpte == 0) {
3947 prevptrstdx = 0;
3948 prevptrsptr = 0;
3949 return 0; /* we know nothing about what this pointer targets */
3950 }
3951
3952 switch (FPTE_TYPE(ptrpte)) {
3953 case TT_PSYM:
3954 *ptag = 5;
3955 *pid = FPTE_SPTR(ptrpte);
3956 return 1;
3957 case TT_ISYM: /* somewhere in the symbol */
3958 *ptag = 6;
3959 *pid = FPTE_SPTR(ptrpte);
3960 return 1;
3961 case TT_GDYN:
3962 case TT_IGDYN:
3963 *ptag = 3;
3964 *pid = FPTE_VAL(ptrpte);
3965 return 1;
3966 case TT_LDYN:
3967 case TT_ILDYN: /* somewhere in the allocated space */
3968 *ptag = 2;
3969 *pid = FPTE_VAL(ptrpte);
3970 return 1;
3971 case TT_CON:
3972 *ptag = 1;
3973 *pid = 0;
3974 return 1;
3975 case TT_ANON: /* don't know where */
3976 case TT_NLOC: /* some nonlocal symbol */
3977 case TT_UNK: /* anywhere */
3978 case TT_UNINIT: /* anywhere */
3979 *ptag = 1;
3980 *pid = 0;
3981 return 1;
3982 case TT_IND: /* some indirect location, shouldn't happen here */
3983 case TT_IIND:
3984 case TT_MEM:
3985 case TT_GLOB:
3986 default:
3987 *ptag = 1;
3988 *pid = 0;
3989 return 1;
3990 }
3991} /* pta_target */

4187/** \brief Do dataflow analysis to determine pointer target information
4188 store pointer target information at loads and stores
4189
4190 - build flow graph
4191 - build reverse depth-first ordering
4192 - build pseudo-assignments to represent pointer modifications
4193 - use data-flow analysis to propagate pointer information around flow graph
4194 - modify the ILI/NME to represent the propagated information
4195
4196 For F90.
4197 */
4198void
4199points_to(void)
4200{
4201 int r, v, rdfohigh, nextrdfohigh, rdfolow, nextrdfolow;
4202 PSI_P succ;
4203 int sl, psdx, offset, iteration, asx;
4204 int stdx, change;
4205
4206 /* initialize */
4207 init_points_to_prop();
4208
4209 /* can we afford to build the data flow equations?
4210 * we will need a word for each critical basic block for a
4211 * pointer target list head for each PSD; also a structure to
4212 * to store lists of actual pointer targets */
4213 head.stg_size = opt.num_nodes * gpsd.nslots + 1;
4214 if (head.stg_size > 1000000) {
4215 /* abort */
4216 Trace(("pointer target analysis is too expensive, abort\n"));
4217 fini_points_to_prop();
4218 return;
4219 }
4220 STG_ALLOC(head, head.stg_size);
4221 NEW(nodeoffset, int, opt.num_nodes + 1);
4222 BZERO(nodeoffset, int, opt.num_nodes + 1);
4223 NEW(localhead, int, gpsd.nslots + 1);
4224 NEW(gpsd.slot, int, gpsd.nslots + 1);
4225 BZERO(gpsd.slot, int, gpsd.nslots + 1);
4226
4227 /* assign a slot number to each pointer, called a PSD or pointer source
4228 * descriptor.
4229 * For Fortran, these are pretty simple */
4230 for (psdx = 1; psdx < gpsd.stg_avail; ++psdx) {
4231 if (PSD_SLOT(psdx))
4232 SLOT(PSD_SLOT(psdx)) = psdx;
4233 }
4234
4235 offset = 1;
4236 /* to simplify memory allocation, we allocate one big vector to hold
4237 * a matrix of information. Here, we give the index into the vector
4238 * for the information for each flow graph node */
4239 /* fill in nodeoffset */
4240 for (r = rdfocount; r > 0; --r) {
4241 v = RDFO(r);
4242 nodeoffset[v] = offset;
4243 offset += gpsd.nslots;
4244 /* default information is 'TOP', points to nothing */
4245 for (sl = 1; sl < gpsd.nslots; ++sl)
4246 HEAD(v, sl) = TTE_NULL;
4247 }
4248 v = RDFO(rdfocount); /* entry node */
4249 /*
4250 * interpret the init assignments at the start node
4251 * Start out by assuming the pointers are all empty
4252 */
4253 for (sl = 0; sl < gpsd.nslots; ++sl) {
4254 HEAD(v, sl) = TPTE_NULL;
4255 LHEAD(sl) = TPTE_NULL;
4256 }
4257 for (asx = FIRSTAS(0); asx > 0 && ASTYPE(asx) == AS_INIT; asx = ASNEXT(asx)) {
4258 interpret(asx);
4259 }
4260 /*
4261 * For any nonlocal pointers that have no initial information,
4262 * assume they start out pointing to any nonlocal
4263 */
4264 for (sl = 1; sl < gpsd.nslots; ++sl) {
4265 psdx = SLOT(sl);
4266 if (LHEAD(sl) != TPTE_NULL) {
4267 HEAD(v, sl) = LHEAD(sl);
4268 } else if (is_source_nonlocal(psdx)) {
4269 HEAD(v, sl) = get_pte(TT_NLOC, 0, 0, 0);
4270 } else {
4271 HEAD(v, sl) = TPTE_UNINIT;
4272 }
4273 /* reinitialize LHEAD */
4274 LHEAD(sl) = TPTE_NULL;
4275 }
4276
4277 /* repeat until no changes, first iteration must visit all nodes */
4278 nextrdfohigh = rdfocount;
4279 nextrdfolow = 1;
4280 iteration = 0;
4281 do {
4282 ++iteration;
4283 rdfohigh = nextrdfohigh;
4284 rdfolow = nextrdfolow;
4285 nextrdfohigh = 0;
4286 nextrdfolow = rdfocount;
4287 Trace(("------------------------"));
4288 Trace(("iteration %d, node positions %d:%d", iteration, rdfohigh, rdfolow));
4289#if DEBUG
4290 check_pte("TPTE error: before iterating");
4291#endif
4292 /* visit each basic block
4293 * symbolically execute each assignment, see how it
4294 * affects the local pointer target information */
4295 for (r = rdfohigh; r >= rdfolow; --r) {
4296 v = RDFO(r);
4297 Trace(("%4d=r, fg:%d, bih:%d", r, v, FG_TO_BIH(v)));
4298 for (sl = 1; sl < gpsd.nslots; ++sl) {
4299 free_list_slot(sl);
4300 LHEAD(sl) = copy_list(HEAD(v, sl));
4301 }
4302#if DEBUG
4303 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
4304 Trace(("before node %d block %d std %d:%d", v, FG_TO_BIH(v),
4305 FG_STDFIRST(v), FG_STDLAST(v)));
4306 puttargets();
4307 }
4308#endif
4309 for (stdx = FG_STDFIRST(v); stdx; stdx = STD_NEXT(stdx)) {
4310#if DEBUG
4311 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
4312 dstdp(stdx);
4313 }
4314#endif
4315 for (asx = FIRSTAS(stdx); asx > 0; asx = ASNEXT(asx)) {
4316 interpret(asx);
4317 }
4318 if (stdx == FG_STDLAST(v))
4319 break;
4320 }
4321#if DEBUG
4322 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
4323 Trace(("after node %d block %d", v, FG_TO_BIH(v)));
4324 puttargets();
4325 }
4326#endif
4327 for (succ = FG_SUCC(v); succ != PSI_P_NULL; succ = PSI_NEXT(succ)) {
4328 int s, sr;
4329 s = PSI_NODE(succ);
4330 Trace(("flow edge from node %d -> %d", v, s));
4331 if (1 /*critical(s)*/) {
4332 if (pte_changed(s)) {
4333 sr = RDFONUM(s);
4334 if (sr >= r && sr > nextrdfohigh) {
4335 /* must iterate again at least from sr */
4336 nextrdfohigh = sr;
4337 if (sr < nextrdfolow)
4338 nextrdfolow = sr;
4339 } else if (sr < rdfolow) {
4340 rdfolow = sr; /* keep going to 'sr' in this iteration */
4341 } else if (sr < nextrdfolow) {
4342 nextrdfolow = sr;
4343 }
4344 }
4345 }
4346 }
4347 }
4348 for (sl = 1; sl < gpsd.nslots; ++sl) {
4349 free_list_slot(sl);
4350 LHEAD(sl) = TTE_NULL;
4351 }
4352 } while (nextrdfohigh >= nextrdfolow);
4353#if DEBUG
4354 check_pte("TPTE error: done iterating");
4355 Trace(("POINTSTO - %5d NME, %5d PSD, %5d SLOTS, %5d APTE, %5d BLOCKS",
4356 nmeb.stg_avail, gpsd.stg_avail, gpsd.nslots, apte.stg_avail,
4357 opt.num_nodes));
4358#endif
4359
4360 /* now modify the STDs */
4361 asx = 0;
4362 gcount.tot = 0;
4363 gcount.ntot = 0;
4364 f90_init();
4365 for (r = rdfocount; r >= 1; --r) {
4366 v = RDFO(r);
4367 Trace(("------------------------"));
4368 Trace(("insert %4d=r, fg:%d", r, v));
4369 for (sl = 1; sl < gpsd.nslots; ++sl) {
4370 free_list_slot(sl);
4371 LHEAD(sl) = copy_list(HEAD(v, sl));
4372 }
4373 if (asx > 0) {
4374 /* real error, didn't finish assignments from previous block */
4375 interr("pointsto: didn't finish all symbolic assignments", asx, ERR_Fatal);
4376 }
4377#if DEBUG
4378 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
4379 Trace(("before node %d stds %d:%d", v, FG_STDFIRST(v), FG_STDLAST(v)));
4380 puttargets();
4381 }
4382#endif
4383 change = 1;
4384 for (stdx = FG_STDFIRST(v); stdx; stdx = STD_NEXT(stdx)) {
4385 set_std_pta(stdx, change);
4386#if DEBUG
4387 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
4388 if (change) {
4389 putstdpta(stdx);
4390 } else {
4391 if (STD_PTA(stdx)) {
4392 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "pta(std=%d) same as std %d\n", stdx,
4393 STD_PREV(stdx));
4394 }
4395 }
4396 }
4397#endif
4398 if (stdx == FG_STDLAST(v)) {
4399 asx = 0;
4400 break;
4401 }
4402 change = 0;
4403 for (asx = FIRSTAS(stdx); asx > 0; asx = ASNEXT(asx)) {
4404 if (ASTYPE(asx) != AS_INIT) {
4405 change = 1;
4406 interpret(asx);
4407 }
4408 }
4409 }
4410 }
4411 fini_points_to_prop();
4412#if DEBUG
4413 if (DBGBIT(TRACEFLAG, TRACEBIT)) {
4414 dstdps(0, 0);
4415 }
4416#endif
4417} /* points_to for F90 */
